title: apple crumb cake
directions: Work flour, 1 cup sugar, butter and salt.
Do not add water. Pat 3/4 mixture on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan or cookie sheet, ungreased.
Add sliced apples; sprinkle lightly with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over apples.
Place pat of butter here and there.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: madeline's tamale balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls about the size of a quarter.
Bring 5 cups of tomato juice and 2 tablespoons of chili powder to boil.
Drop balls into mixture and simmer 30 minutes.

title: crunchy topper
directions: Combine and mix well.
Brown in heavy skillet over medium heat, about 5 minutes.
Spread out on cookie sheet to cool. Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: peas for large family
directions: Shell peas until you get 2 quarts.
Pick out all the bad peas and discard.
Wash peas through 3 or 4 pans of water.
Put in a 4-quart pot or dishpan.
Add water 2 inches above peas.
Slice salt pork crossways down to rind in 1/4-inch slices.
Put in pot of peas; cover and boil until peas are tender.
Add sugar to peas while boiling.
You may have to add more water before peas are done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple and pudding in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well.
Put in a covered dish and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl combine sugar, margarine, cream cheese, salt, almond extract, vanilla and egg yolk; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough 1/3 at a time to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with lightly floured cookie cutters.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Leave cookies plain or, if desired, brush with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely.
Frost and decorate, if desired.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: onion-mushroom meat loaf(makes great sandwiches)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and stir and blend until well mixed.
Pour into loaf pan or dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove and serve.
Wonderful served with baked potato. Recipe makes 8 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: potato pie
directions: Grate potatoes in milk to prevent discoloring.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake as for custard for 45 minutes at 350° or until knife comes out clean when tested. Bake in 9-inch pan.
This tastes like coconut custard.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add corn syrup and sugar.
Stir in salt and vanilla. Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour pecans into pie shell.
Stir melted butter into syrup.
Pour into shell.
Make sure pecans rise to top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter, oil, sugar, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs together until smooth.
Sift soda, flour, cream of tartar and salt together.
Add to first mixture gradually.
Roll out into small balls and press onto cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients with meat. Make sure hands are moist with water so the meat will not stick to hands. With hands or spoon pinch away parts of meat and roll with hands; then season meat. They can be large or small. Cook meatballs in skillet until done. Add to your favorite sauce.

title: holiday biscotti
directions: Beat butter or margarine in a mixing bowl for 30 seconds.
Add sugar, baking powder, baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt; beat until combined.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer.
Stir in remaining flour, anise and fennel seeds, cranberries, pistachios and apricots.
Turn mixture out onto a lightly floured board. Cover and refrigerate for several hours or until easy to handle.

title: pear delight
directions: Boil 1 cup of the pear juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in the juice. Soften the cream cheese or blend with juice until smooth.
Fold all.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: hot rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly in yeast water.
Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Knead well and make into rolls.
Let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yum a getta
directions: Brown beef; add onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until onion is tender.
Add sugar and tomato soup; mix well and set aside.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add chicken soup.
Place layer in casserole.
Place cheese layer on top.
Cover with meat mixture and then cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and heated through.

title: canadian war cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients; boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool. Add plain flour.
Add baking soda in hot water.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Bake in 4 (9-inch) cake pans at 325°, until done, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Mix and add 1 pint of milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.
Bake in crust same as custard at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: quick and easy italian chicken
directions: Pour bottle of dressing over chicken.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator (covered).
Pour chicken and Italian dressing in large pan and fry until done, about 10 minutes.

title: fresh peaches and dumplings
directions: Combine peaches, water, sugar and lemon juice in 3-quart pan. Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes, then combine pancake mix, brown sugar, nutmeg, milk and butter. Stir together.
Remove peach mixture from heat. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dumpling batter onto hot peach mixture.
Cover pan and return to heat for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: old fashioned ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar gradually, then Eagle Brand, cream and vanilla flavor, then whole milk.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: 7-up miniature fruitcakes
directions: Combine dates and 7-Up in a large pan; heat to boiling.
Cool a little.
Add soda, sugar, butter, egg, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in fruits and nuts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer hamburger in bottom of baking dish.
One row of onions and Tater Tots.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, vanilla, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl; beat until smooth.
Serve with fruit slices or cookies.
Chill, tightly covered.
Yields 8 (1 ounce) servings.

title: mousse
directions: First Layer:
Mix
the
flour,
butter and nuts and pat into the bottom of a large, oblong glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes; cool.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a full boil (a boil that can't be stirred down).
Time it 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chips and marshmallows.
Stir until thick.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: oven baked peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add flour and milk and cook until smooth.
Cut
mushrooms and pimento;
add to sauce.
Add cheese, Worcestershire.
Cook
until cheese melts.
Add peas. Pour in casserole, top with crumbs, dot with butter; sprinkle a dash of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss cheese bake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm sesame bread sticks.
Also excellent as a dip for vegetables.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and bake in an ungreased angel food pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Do not grease pan.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, 1 cup.
Add flour.
Mix 1 cup at a time until climbs up in beaters.
Knead to center until thick. Turn over and put into greased bowl.
Let rise 1 hour.
Make into rolls.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add the cream cheese to pudding. Put pudding mixture on top of Twinkies.
Add Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: grandma davidson's custard pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add pinch of salt, vanilla and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into the creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: beef hawaiian
directions: Chop onion.
Slice celery and carrots.
Brown hamburg and onion.
Add 2 cups water, carrots and celery; cook until tender. Add mushroom soup and soy sauce to taste.
Heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sweet and sour meatball salad
directions: Prepare Sesame Oven Meatballs as directed.
In a large bowl, combine meatballs, green pepper, carrots, celery, water chestnuts and pineapple; set aside.
In a small pan, combine cornstarch, brown sugar, ginger, red pepper (if desired), soy, vinegar and broth; mix until smooth.
Place over high heat and cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Pour over meatball mixture and stir gently to coat evenly.
Divide lettuce evenly among 4 to 6 dinner plates.
Top lettuce with noodles; then spoon meatball mixture evenly over each serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix jello with boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Add cold water and fruit juices.
Pour over ice and add ginger ale just before serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in shallow casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with small bread or sesame sticks.

title: chewy coconut cookies
directions: Cream oleo; add sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well, then add coconut, nuts and vanilla. Drop by large teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies should be chewy.
These cookies freeze well.

title: sparkling limeade
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar to the lime juice and stir until the sugar is dissolved. Add sparkling water. Stir and taste for sweetness. Add more sugar if desired. Pour over ice and serve. The sparkling water must be added at the last minute. Complements mexican dishes.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread beans on a 12-inch round tray.
Mix avocados and lemon juice.
Spread over beans.
Blend sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning and spread over avocados.
Sprinkle tomatoes and green onions over sour cream mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and garnish with ripe olives.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: In large frypan, cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Add cabbage and salt to this.
Turn cabbage until coated with drippings. Cover and cook 7 minutes.
Add your cooked noodles and stir.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds and cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until bubbly (about 25 minutes).
Top with almonds and cheese and serve hot with crackers.

title: lemon-herb turkey cutlets
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; sprinkle over both sides of cutlets and set aside.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cover rhubarb with boiling water.
Immediately drain.
Stir marmalade through rhubarb and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread rhubarb-marmalade mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until browned.
Frost with powdered sugar icing if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; tear into bite-sized pieces.
In an 11 x 9-inch casserole dish, crush 1 1/2 rolls of the crackers and melt stick of margarine; pour on crackers.
Place on top of cracker mixture 2 or 3 cuts of the deboned chicken.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and water chestnuts together and pour on top of chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crush a few more crackers to go on the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat to boiling point in saucepan the water and butter.
Lower heat to simmering.
Stir in flour until mixture leaves the pan and forms into a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat and then cool about 1 hour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until velvety smooth.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until dry and light brown, 45 to 50 minutes. Cool on rack or on aluminum foil with paper underneath.
Store in covered container or freeze.
Cut through middle; fill with pudding as a dessert or meat salad as a finger sandwich.
Makes about 8 large or 12 medium puffs.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Layer, in pie
shell,
mushrooms and Swiss cheese.
Top with spinach souffle.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to box in 2 (8-inch) pans.
Mix jello with boiling water, then add frozen berries and cold water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Make pudding as directed on box.
Split cakes in half.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Melt caramels with cream in a double boiler or microwave.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Pour caramel mixture over cereal mixture; mix together.
Butter hands and roll into small balls. Let them set up on wax paper.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix first five ingredients well in mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add vinegar and celery seed.
Beat lightly and chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps well for weeks, but won't last that long.

title: scandinavian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into walnut size balls.
Brown in shortening.
They burn easily.

title: pizza sauce(to can)
directions: Cook tomatoes and garlic together and put through sieve, then chop and cook in vegetable oil, onions and peppers.
Keep well stirred and add this to tomato juice.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer all together until it comes to a boil, then fill jars and seal.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly pour in hot milk.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Cook 10 minutes at 450°, then 35 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Line pie pan with your favorite pastry.
Arrange pecans over pastry.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients, beating well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell over the pecans and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: Place
carrots	in
quart casserole dish.
Add brown sugar and
butter.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, covered. Stir and recover
and cook additional 5 minutes on High.
Mix water and cornstarch.
Stir in cornstarch and nuts.
Microwave on High until
carrot
mixture has thickened, 3 to 4 minutes. Serves 4.

title: smothered hamburger steak
directions: Combine the ground beef, salt, pepper, water and bread crumbs; mix well.
Shape into six patties.
Brown in oil on one side, turn and top with onion and gravy.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: turkey and rice soup(quick-to-fix)
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven combine chicken broth, water, rosemary and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in mixed vegetables and rice.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender.
Stir in turkey or chicken and undrained tomatoes.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in sauce a few hours.
(You may skip this, if necessary.)
Bake until tender in sauce.
Add some cornstarch to thicken before serving over cooked rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for 35 minutes at 300°.

title: quick salad dressing
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or more.

title: bread machine white bread
directions: Add liquids first, then add dry ingredients.
Do on a 1 1/2 pound loaf white bread cycle.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: everything but the kitchen sink cookies
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together in a mixer.
Then add the
next
ingredients.
Mix
well, then add the chips, pecans and
M&M's.
Mix
all together in a large pan.
Use ice cream scoop
and place scoopfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Cookies will be 3 to 4 inches.
Bake at 350° until done (about 15 minutes).

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening with fingertips.
Push mixture to sides of bowl.
Add milk in center; mix gently with fork.
Toss lightly on floured board.
Pat down to about 1-inch thickness.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned (12 to 15 minutes).

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix together Bisquick, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Add applesauce, milk, eggs and oil.
Stir well.
Add to first mixture.
Fill a baking pan (greased and floured or lined with muffin papers) 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Dip muffins into melted butter and then into 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar mixture.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with pie filling and chill at least 3 hours or overnight, before serving.

title: scotcharoos
directions: In a 2 quart pan, mix Karo and sugar.
Bring to a bubbling boil.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pyrex pan which has been oiled or rubbed with butter.
Melt both kinds of chips and spread over top of mixture.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: mandarin-pineapple cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oranges with juice, oil and eggs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown together ground
beef
and
onion.
Add all other ingredients except tortillas and cheese; mix well.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in cupcake papers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins; 6 muffins is equal to 1 serving.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix water and margarine in large bowl until margarine is melted.
Stir in stuffing or cornbread just to moisten; set aside. Brown meat; stir in chili powder, beans, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes. Spray dish with Pam.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Spoon stuffing evenly over top.
Bake 25 minutes until heated through. Garnish as desired.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add juices and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour into milk jugs (not too full because it will expand) and freeze.

title: vegetable pull-apart bread
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and zucchini in margarine until tender about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add bacon.
Separate rolls into thin layers.

Place 1 layer in the bottom of a Bundt or tube pan. Sprinkle with part of the Parmesan cheese and vegetable mixture. Continue layering rolls, Parmesan cheese and vegetable mixture. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except salad oil, flour, spice and cheese. Shape into large meatballs with 1 cube of the cheese in the center of each, making sure cheese is completely covered with the meat. Coat each meatball with mixture of flour and spice.
Brown over medium-high in skillet with salad oil.
Place browned meatballs in large casserole and add pizza sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Scatter shredded Mozzarella cheese over all of it just 5 minutes before removing from oven.
May be served with rice or spaghetti noodles.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, minced onions, barbecue chips, egg, milk and meat loaf mix together.
Make into balls.
Put on cookie sheet; bake at 450° until brown.
Heat the chili sauce and grape juice. Cook in a slow cooker for 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low.

title: sue's easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (add a little honey to water).
Stir in 2 cups flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Beat batter; add remaining flour and mix with a spoon.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise, loosely covered, 25 minutes or until doubled in size.
Shape as desired.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 20 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: Combine in a saucepan, the vinegar, salt, dry mustard, celery seed, salad oil and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool. Combine cole slaw and chopped onions.
Pour cooled dressing over slaw and onion mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of about a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together; pour on top of margarine.
Then pour blueberries on top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break noodles into pieces and cook in boiling water and drain. Put chicken, pimento, green pepper and chopped onion in a casserole dish.
Mix water and soup; add to chicken mixture.
Add 1 1/4 cups cheese and noodles.
Season to taste.
Toss lightly and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: steak fried rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop the 4 boneless steaks in some squares; brown them in oven on a cookie sheet.
Put the stir-fried vegetables in a hot, large frying pan with the 2 tablespoons of oil.
Stir occasionally.
Add bell peppers and onion; cook vegetables until tender.
Put the cooked rice in the pan; stir it all together.
Take the brown meat out and add it in the pan; stir it.
Let it cook for 3 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Spoon cottage cheese into oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O powder over cottage cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add pineapple.
Stir well,
Fold in Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Fill jar with cucumbers.
Mix all but sugar.
Fill jar with cold water and seal tightly.
After 2 months or more, pour off liquid and throw away.
Slice pickles lengthwise.
Add sugar and let stand 24 hours.
Before using, liquid will form as sugar dissolves.
They can then be resealed and will keep indefinitely.

title: strawberry-cranberry jello salad
directions: Cook cranberries, strawberries with water until berries pop. Add unflavored gelatin and jello, stir till all dissolved. Add the crushed pineapple, stir to combine. Pour into 8 dishes or 1 serving bowl. Chill.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Start out blending on low, then on medium speed, then on high speed until mixture is as creamy as possible.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Refrigerate until pie is very firm.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Mix well until texture is semi-stiff, like cookie dough.
Press into well-greased baking pan (oblong 13 1/2 x 2-inch pan approximately).
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar well. Pour on top of first mixture and bake for 1 hour.
Let cool approximately 1 hour before serving.
Cut in squares.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cut the very tips of 1 bunch of broccoli.
Cover with water and cook for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 stick margarine.

title: chocolate microwave pies(make 2 pies)
directions: For each s'more, spread 1 graham cracker square with about 2 teaspoons peanut butter.
Top with about 9 semi-sweet chocolate pieces and about 6 tiny or 1 large marshmallow.
Cover with another graham cracker square; wrap loosely in paper toweling. Microcook until chocolate and marshmallows melt, about 1 minute for one s'more or 1 to 1 1/2 minutes for four s'mores.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut the citron, apricots and pineapple in large pieces, leaving the cherries whole.
Seed the raisins, and wash and dry the currants.
Cream the butter and sugar, add the yolks of eggs well beaten, then the fruit, also the flour, salt, baking powder and spices sifted together; put in the brandy and mix all thoroughly.
Last of all, add the stiffly beaten whites of the eggs.
Turn into greased cake pans and steam five hours; afterwards bake very slowly for one hour to slightly dry the cake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add all other ingredients and simmer, covered, over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mom's tangy french dressing
directions: Blend
all
ingredients in a blender, adding Wesson oil last.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; cook and stir until thick. Cool completely.
Line a buttered pie pan with whole vanilla wafers, crumbling a few to fill bare spots for better fit.
Add ice cream.
Top with the chocolate sauce and freeze.
Add crushed nuts to top.
Easy, but very good!
Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix and put in roaster; cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours. Remove from oven.
Add 1 cup sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: sausage and apple breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and take out on paper towel. Leave fat in skillet. Fry apples in fat for a few minutes until they are somewhat soft and colored. Beat eggs. Trim crust off bread and cut into cubes. Add milk, cheese and mustard to eggs and combine well. Stir in bread and apples. Put sausage in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Pour egg mixture over sausage. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°. Cover for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: mexican or seven-layer dip
directions: Pit and mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip in bottom of 9 x 13-inch shallow pan.
Spread avocado mixture. Spread sour cream mixture.
Spread green onion on top.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and black olives.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
May be made the day before.
If fresh avocados are not available, you may substitute an avocado dip.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute chopped vegetables until soft.
Add potatoes and broth.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
In a separate saucepan, melt 1 stick butter, stir in flour and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add cream slowly, stirring all the while. Cook and stir over low to medium heat until very thick (about 20 minutes).
Add cream sauce to potatoes and stir to blend.
Add salt, pepper and a little nutmeg to taste.
Soup is best if cooled and reheated.

title: broccoli, rice, cheese and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Mix in the instant rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until onion is beginning to be transparent.
Do not brown.
Add frozen broccoli.
Cook for a few minutes (until broccoli is not frozen).
Stir in soup and milk.
Heat until it begins to simmer.
Add cheese to hot mixture.
In a 9x13 inch baking dish, mix the prepared rice, cream of chicken soup, butter, milk, broccoli, onion and cheese.
Bake for 30-35 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and top is lightly brown.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and deviled ham in bowl; mix well.
Add relish, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: red cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Make paste with eggs and food coloring.
Add salt, buttermilk and flour to mixture.
Mix vanilla, vinegar and soda together; fold into cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing for 1 hour.
Then wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken breast.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine sour cream and soup and mix well.
Lay a thin layer (about half) of the chipped beef in baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of beef and place rest of beef around or on top of chicken.
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
A few minutes before serving, add cheese on top of chicken and return to oven for five minutes.
Serves 8.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until translucent.
Layer onions and Ritz in casserole dish, beginning and ending with Ritz.
Add milk to margarine.
Pour over dish.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 325. Add cheese and melt.

title: beans, beans, beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add beans and all other ingredients.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 2 hours, or 350° for 1 hour.

title: johnny appleseed bars
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add everything else except for the apples and pecans, then beat mixture until smooth (about 2 minutes).
Press 1/2 of dough into bottom of a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle pecans over dough.
Arrange apple slices over pecans.
Roll remaining dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper to form a 9-inch square. Remove top sheet; place over filling.
Remove other sheet.
Press lightly around edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: honey brown bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Scald milk.
Add oleo, salt and honey.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture. Add whole wheat flour.
Add white flour, a cup at
a time.

title: grilled veggie delight
directions: Heat grill or oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine vegetables. Add oil and lemon juice.
Toss to coat evenly.
Place vegetables on grill pan or roasting pan.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender, turning occasionally.
Season with sea salt and pepper, if desired.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix in casserole.
Cover with crushed potato chips, chopped parsley and cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: never-fail pecan pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Pour into
unbaked
pie shell and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: pretzel-jello salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: party tea
directions: Mix all together and serve chilled.
Great for children's parties.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Cream together first 8 ingredients and spread like pizza crust on large cake plate or regular plate.
Spread cocktail sauce on this.
Spread small or chopped boiled shrimp on cocktail sauce. Sprinkle parsley flakes and oregano on top.
Serve with Ritz crackers, etc.
Can use packaged frozen shrimp.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Divide drippings in thirds.
Cook eggs in first drippings; take out of pan.
Add second drippings and cook vegetables.
Remove; add third drippings and stir-fry rice.
Add eggs and vegetables to rice.
Add seasoning.

title: spiced iced tea
directions: Serve hot or cold.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour.
Slice off top of potatoes. Spoon out potato being careful to keep shells whole.
Combine potato, butter, salt and garlic salt.
Mash, adding enough milk to make fluffy.
Fold in cream cheese, onion, parsley and spoon potato mixture back into potato shells.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Refrigerate overnight. Put into 450° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Cook 1 minute. Beat egg yolks.

Gradually stir about 1/4 of the hot mixture into yolks. Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly. Cook, stirring constantly, 30 seconds. Remove from heat. Stir in butter, vanilla and 1 cup flaked coconut.
Pour into pastry shell. Cool completely. Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Beat whipping cream at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add powdered sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until soft peaks form. Pipe onto pie.
Garnish, if desired. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Place water and salt in bowl. Mix yeast in dry cake mix.

Add to water mixture. Add eggs and mix. Add flour. Mix and knead until smooth. May need more flour. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size. Shape in rolls; let stand until double in size. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Can be used as sweet rolls.

title: cabbage meat skillet
directions: Saute meat and onions about 10 minutes.
Pour off liquids, if desired.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add cabbage and rice.
Stir together, mixing well. Cover; continue to cook 18 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Bring milk to scalding point.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Cook over hot water, stirring, about 10 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add egg yolks slowly, beating all the time. Cook until thick.
Cool. Add vanilla. Fold in coconut. Pour into pie crust.
Cover with meringue. Bake until brown at 325°.
(You can cook this mixture in microwave for 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, using large dish.)

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Press 3/4 of mixture in nongreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips.
Melt caramels and cream in pan.
Pour over chips and nuts.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs and mixture on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dinner muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix the milk and remaining ingredients in a blender at low speed, then add to dry ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Line muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked cheesy chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, spoon into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add the Jell-O. When the mixture begins to set up, pour over sliced strawberries that have been arranged in a pre-baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add eggs last.
Shape into loaf and bake in 375 degree oven 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour in large pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
If extra fat comes to the top while baking, pour off.
Use less cayenne pepper if you don't want it so hot.

title: easy apple salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice over apple to keep from turning.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease a 6-cup casserole dish.
In a large bowl, combine the corn, eggs, milk, sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour into the prepared dish.
Combine the bread crumbs and melted butter, tossing well.
Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake in a 300° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Saute in oleo the celery, green pepper and onion.
In saucepan, mix mushroom soup, water, Velveeta cheese and ham.
In another pan cook egg noodles according to package directions. Drain the noodles and pour into a large baking pan.
Blend soup mix and vegetables together and pour over egg noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls (walnut size) and press centers with your thumb, fill centers with jelly.

title: farmer's market meal
directions: Slice cooked sausage into bite-sized pieces.
Combine all remaining ingredients and place everything in casserole dish. Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until done (heated through with cheese melted).

title: quick peach pie
directions: Press 1/2 of crumbs in pie plate.
Fill with canned peaches, drained.
Spread rest of crumbs on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Beat together flour, milk, sugar, baking powder and salt. Melt butter in pan.
Pour batter in pan, then add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: viennese steam pudding with souffle sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased mold with tight fitting cover. Set into pot with water level below top of mold and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cajun casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
The mixture should be the consistency of dressing.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, pepper and onion slowly until sausage is done. Add the other ingredients.
Stir and cook 10 minutes, covered. Uncover and cook 10 minutes more.
Pour into dish and serve.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Simmer the milk, butter, cocoa and sugar in pan on low heat. When completely mixed, remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour onto a square baking pan (well buttered).
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: cloud pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, pudding and lemon juice.
Add pineapple and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared pie crust of choice (great with graham cracker crust).

title: tomatoes, corn and cheese
directions: Fresh corn and tomatoes can also be used.
Put a layer of corn in a buttered baking dish, layer of tomatoes, a layer of cheese and repeat.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top, dot with butter and bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to first mixture.
Roll into walnut size balls with hands and place on baking sheet.
Flatten cookies with hands and mark top with fork tines.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
(May vary with ovens.)

title: brown rice main dish
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat the butter; add onion, cabbage, parsley, garlic and cubes.
Cook gently, mashing cubes with a wooden spoon to break up fine, until vegetables are tender and crisp (about 10 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Reheat.

title: creamed crab-meat dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour and then cream.
Cook until thick.
Stir in egg yolk, then all seasonings.
Fold in crab meat. Serve from chafing dish on thin sliced bread squares, in tiny bread cups, or with Fritos.

title: poor man's pound cake(do not preheat oven.  do not sift ingredients.  do not grease
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, oleo, sugar, milk and eggs in a large bowl.
Blend at high speed of mixer for 10 minutes.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients together thoroughly. Divide the filling and spread evenly over the tortillas; roll up tortillas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends; refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap; cut into 1/2 inch to 3/4 inch slices.
Serve with salsa.

title: basic shortbread
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in vanilla. Combine flour and salt; gradually add to butter mixture beating at low speed until well blended.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2 inch round cutter or Christmas cookie cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 275 degrees for 50 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to a wire rack to cool.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: country-style barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs
into	serving
size
pieces
(3 to 4 ribs per person).
Saute
garlic in butter in a medium saucepan about 5 minutes.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Bring sauce to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Place
ribs,
meaty
side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.	Spoon mixture over ribs.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.	Check after an hour cooking for doneness.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Mix very well and chill overnight.
Make into a log and roll in pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.
If parsley is used, combine with pecans.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water and sugar in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; pour over gelatin in a bowl.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Mix in white grape juice and lemon peel.
Chill until partially set, then whip until light in color.
Whip sour cream until it doubles in volume.
Fold into whipped gelatin and gently mix in sliced strawberries.
Turn into cooled crust and chill until set.
Garnish with whipped cream and whole strawberries.

title: beef steak sierra
directions: Pound first four ingredients into steak with meat pounder or edge of saucer.
Cut into pieces and brown in oil quickly.
Remove all but about 2 tablespoons oil.
Add consomme and let simmer until done.
Add more consomme if needed.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer until it thickens.
Cook noodles until tender, drain, rinse in cold water.

title: mimosa salad
directions: Combine all the vegetables and mix in 4 tablespoons mayonnaise, some salt and pepper and as much nutmeg as your palate desires.
More mayonnaise may be added to achieve a creamier texture.
Chill and serve on a lettuce bed with chopped hard-boiled egg.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix and marinate ingredients for 1 hour.
Serve with nacho chips or Doritos chips.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store
in airtight container.
To serve, mix 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup water.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer each ingredient listed individually.
The Romaine lettuce should be on the bottom layer, followed by the other ingredients.
After all ingredients have been layered, mix the package of Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing and pour over salad.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Place shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar, vanilla and eggs in a bowl and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well and add oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350°
oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from pan.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Combine pork, beef and onion and brown.
In saucepan combine all ingredients (except orzo).
Add water.
Cook for 1 hour on low. Add orzo and stir (making sure it doesn't stick).

title: chicken piccata
directions: Coat chicken cutlets with flour.
In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken and cook about 5 minutes or until lightly browned and tender.
Remove to platter; keep warm.

title: tony's chicken wings
directions: Clean garlic.
If large clove, cut in half and count as two cloves.
In a nonstick skillet pan, heat oil and garlic.
Put in chicken wings and cook until brown and done.
Add, while cooking, your salt and pepper.
Garlic will melt some and caramelize chicken.
Add wine last and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: low-fat cheese and basil biscuits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine milk, cheese and basil; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: mickey rooney's salmon surprise
directions: In small bowl, mix salmon and mayonnaise together, then mash. In separate bowl mix pickle, onion, celery and cabbage leaf.
In large bowl mix macaroni and Cheddar cheese.
Add salmon mixture and pickle mixture to macaroni.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar, croutons and capers.
Mix well.
Add peas.
Chill mixture in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Line 4 separate plates with lettuce. Mound mixture on lettuce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve.

title: nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and continue beating until very stiff.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and baking powder. Fold into egg whites and add vanilla, pecans and salt.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with whipped cream or other whipped topping.
Keep refrigerated.

title: shrimp and crab spread
directions: Mix well all ingredients except cream cheese.
This can be mixed a day ahead of serving if desired.
Right before serving, spread cream cheese flat.
Then pour mixture over the top of the cream cheese.
Serve as an appetizer.
Serves 12-14.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs; add the flour which has been sifted together with the baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add the vanilla and oil.
Fold in chopped nuts and apples.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add sugar and Jell-O.
Bring to a boil.
Cool thoroughly.
Add buttermilk.
After mixture is cold, fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat, drain on paper towel until cool.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a bowl, mix beans, onion, green chilies, tomatoes and meat.
In another bowl, put in lettuce and top with bean mixture, cheese, chips and pour dressing over all and mix well. This dish serves 6 to 8 people.

title: easy party fruit punch
directions: Mix frozen juice concentrates and water in punch bowl.
Five minutes before serving, add ginger ale and ice cubes or ice frozen in ring mold.
Cut orange, lemon and strawberries into thin slices and float in punch.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onions and celery.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: savory potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Combine remaining ingredients; toss with potatoes.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until tender and browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef in large saucepan over medium heat; drain. Add remaining ingredients except corn.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add corn; cook 5 minutes.
Makes 6 one-cup servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Add corn bread mix and fold in. Bake at 36-° for 45-50 minutes -- until a golden crust has formed over all.

title: mom's dill pickles
directions: Boil water, pickling salt and vinegar to a rolling boil.
Put dill on bottom and top of jar.
Take juice off the heat and put on jar packed with pickles.
Put on lid and ring and let set about 14 days in warm place to work or until jar clears the juice.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, butter and salt; mix with hands until thoroughly mixed.
Save 1 cup crumbs; set aside.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 cup molasses, 1 cup hot water and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Mix well; set aside.

title: pepper steak with mushrooms
directions: Brown beef cubes in shortening; remove from pan.
Blend in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add catsup, water, soy sauce, pepper, bouillon cube, garlic and onion; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add beef to sauce; cook until tender.
Add mushrooms, peppers and onions (rings); cook for about 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Do not add salt or Accent. Serve immediately with rice.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about one cup or about the same amount as a can.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Mix ground beef with chopped onion and pepper.
Separate this mixture in half.
Press one half on the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Spread the sauerkraut over that, then spread the other half of the ground beef on top of sauerkraut.
Sprinkle over that the 2 cups of uncooked egg noodles; dollop the soup over noodles, covering completely.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Take out and sprinkle on about a cup of shredded cheese.
Bake for another 1/2 hour; let set for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Put squash and onion in water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit dessert squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch thick slices. Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping, into 14 x 10-inch rectangle on lightly greased foil-lined baking sheet. Press slices together lightly with fingers to form crust. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. Carefully remove foil.

title: baked ziti in white clam sauce
directions: Saute chopped garlic in olive oil.
Add clam sauce; mix with minced clams.
Cook until just boiling.
Cook pasta; drain.
Put into glass pan (coated lightly with oil).
Add pasta sauce.
Turn oven to broil.
Add Mozzarella.
Keep in oven until lightly browned.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 4.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo and flour until crumbly and press lightly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until done.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top crust.
Mix instant pudding, milk and lemon juice.
Spread over top of first mixture.
When set, spread Cool Whip over top.

title: quick skillet lasagna
directions: Cook mostaccioli according to directions.
Beat Ricotta cheese with milk until smooth. Drain pasta and return to pot.
Add Ricotta mixture.
Add Parmesan, sausage and tomato sauce.
Toss to combine.
Set aside for 5 minutes before serving.

title: creamy crab soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Stir in crabmeat, bouillon and pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes.
(Do not boil.) Stir in cooking sherry.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Whisk dry ingredients in a bowl. Mix peanut butter, cream, egg and vanilla extract until smooth. Add to bake mix mixture; stir until blended.

Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Smooth dough with fingertips and press cookies with the back of a fork to flatten. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until browned. Cool on sheets 1 minute before transferring to wire racks to cool completely.

title: cherry pie deluxe
directions: Sprinkle crushed graham crackers in bottom of pie pan.
In bowl whip Dream Whip with cream cheese.
Add marshmallows.
Spread over graham crackers and chill.
When firm, spread cherry pie filling mix over top.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and cabbage.
Add nuts, oranges and dressing. Toss and serve.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with bean dip.
Mix together mayo, sour cream and taco seasoning and layer on top of bean dip. Layer remaining ingredients in the order given.
Serve with taco chips. Serves 6 to 8 people as appetizer.

title: black beans
directions: Wash the beans and soak in water with the green pepper.
When the beans swell, cook in the same water until soft (approximately 45 minutes).
Heat the oil in a frying pan and add onion and garlic, followed by ground green pepper.
Add this along with salt, pepper, oregano, bay leaf and sugar to beans.
Allow to boil for a further hour and add the vinegar and wine, cooking slowly for another hour.
If there is still too much liquid, cook, uncovered, for a while.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil just before serving.
Serves 8 approximately.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix pretzels and butter or oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread cheese mix over pretzels.
Spread Cool Whip over cheese.
Chill.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot pineapple juice; add the strawberries.
Allow to set.
Pour over top and refrigerate.
Most unusual and delicious.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, butter and vanilla together; stir until creamy.
Add oats and eggs; let set for 10 minutes. Mix soda with plain flour; add to other mixture.
Stir in package of chocolate chips.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut soup
directions: Melt butter; add onion and celery. Saute until soft but not brown. Add flour and salt and mix until well blended. Add broth and cook, stirring, until thickened. Continue cooking, covered, for about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and strain. Return to heat; add peanut butter, celery salt and lemon juice and heat to serving temperature. Garnish with chopped peanuts.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well and fold in 3 cups blueberries.
Spread in greased 9 x 13 pan and sprinkle topping over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add milk and mix. Add sour cream and mix. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Cook for appropriate time. Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk, in medium size saucepan. Bring to boil, lower heat and cover. Cook 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove from heat and mash until very fine. Stir in milk and return to stove until hot. (Do not boil.) Makes 6 servings.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 people.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Brown beef or turkey; drain.
Add pasta sauce and mushrooms. Mix together cottage cheese and yogurt.
Spread 1/2 meat sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer each of noodles, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat once.
Pour in water around side of pan. Cover tight with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Pick, shell, look and wash vegetables.	Wash jars and lids in soapy water; rinse and scald in hot water.	Pack peas or beans in jars.
Put 1/2 teaspoon salt to a pint, 1 teaspoon to a quart. Have tips in hot water.
Fill jars with hot water and seal.

title: bean salad
directions: Add all together.
Let stand overnight before serving.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken.
Using the chicken broth, cook noodles.
Mix cream of chicken soup with chicken and noodles.
Add just a little broth. Pour into baking dish and sprinkle crumbled bread crumbs and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandpa's surprise pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring while heating.
Chill well.
Combine softened ice cream and chilled pumpkin mixture.
Spoon into pie crust. Freeze firm.
Preparation time:
20 to 30 minutes.
Must be frozen.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix
together
flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, oil, sour
cream
or buttermilk with soda mixed in.
Mix well, add boiling
water and mix, then add vanilla.
Use greased and floured cake
pans.
Makes
excellent cupcakes (bake these 15 minutes). Bake cake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken pineapple stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
In large skillet, stir-fry chicken with garlic and ginger in oil for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, carrots and bell pepper.
Cover; steam 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Pour into skillet; add green onions and toss until heated through.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with half of the grated cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with remaining half of the grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dip for corn chips
directions: Mix all the ingredients, serve with corn chips.

title: puppy chow treats
directions: Melt in large saucepan the margarine and chocolate chips.
Mix in cereal and let cool.
In a brown bag, pour in powdered sugar and ingredients and shake well.
It's important not to use plastic bag because the ingredients will melt bag.
You need to mix while warm so powdered sugar will stick.

title: brownie cake and frosting
directions: In saucepan, bring oleo, water and cocoa to boil.
In mixing bowl, sift sugar, flour and salt together.
Pour hot mixture into flour mixture and beat well until mixed.
Add sour cream, eggs and baking soda.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: real strawberry jelly
directions: In large pot, pour strawberry juice and add your Sure-Jell. Bring to hard boil. Once this is done, add your sugar to the pot and reboil. Boil 1 minute on hard boil to where you can't stir down. Remove the skim off the top after settling. Have jars hot in boiling water, the lids and seals dry. Fill jars and return to boiling water for 5 minutes. Take out and set aside to let cool. Gently press the top of the lid to seal.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Tastes like chicken salad.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir zucchini and vanilla into mixture.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into balls or place in small plastic bowl to form.
Remove to plate when serving.
Surround with favorite crackers.
Make several hours ahead of party.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Whisk together all ingredients except sugar and oil.
Add the sugar by the spoonful and continue whisking.
Slowly whisk in the oil by the spoonful, stopping when the dressing has reached the desired consistency and taste.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, in large mixing bowl. Beat at low speed for 30 seconds and medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple, juice of lemon and sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water 5 minutes; add to hot mixture.
When cool, add grated cheese and whipped cream.
Pour in greased mold.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: basic pizza crust
directions: In large bowl, dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 3/4 cups flour, salt and oil.
Mix to form a soft ball.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine milk and bread crumbs in a large bowl and allow to soak for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes, until firm in center and a golden brown.
Cool in the pan and cut into squares.
May be served plain or with a sauce as a dessert.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large baking dish, combine all of the ingredients. Stir until blended. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until heated through.

title: chocolate chip zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Add sugar, vegetable oil, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly but well. Combine flour, salt, soda, powder and cinnamon.
Add to mixture. Stir well. Add the chocolate chips.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans (pans should be greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Melt butter; add flour and salt; blend.
Add broth, giblets and eggs.
Cook until thick, stir constantly.
(I add a dash of black pepper.)

title: cocoa swirl coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse.
Add eggs, orange juice and orange peel; stir to blend.
Then combine confectioners sugar, nuts and cocoa in a small bowl.
Stir in butter that's melted.
Spread 3/4 in a greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of crumb mix over batter.
Spread on 1 cup batter and sprinkle with remaining crumb mix.
Cover with batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with orange glaze.

title: braised chuck steak
directions: Roll steak in flour.
In heavy kettle, add oil and brown both sides of steak.
Add tomato paste, water, onion soup mix, caraway seed and bay leaves.
Cook slowly until fork-tender.
Good in crock-pot.

title: creamed onions
directions: In large saucepan, boil onions in salt water.
Drain and set aside.
In same pan, melt butter.
Blend in flour and salt until smooth.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Stir in cloves, parsley and onions.
Stir until gently heated.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, then drain. Mix well with bell pepper and onion. Combine soup, Wesson oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce, then pour mixture over carrots, bell pepper and onion. Refrigerate.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: my easy chicken chow mein(2 servings)
directions: Wash and slice chicken into small slices; stir-fry in 1 tablespoon oil until done.
Add 3 teaspoons soy sauce; stir well and set aside.
In another pan, stir-fry cabbage in remaining oil until limp.
Add 2 tablespoons of soy sauce and 1/2 package of seasoning mix which comes with the Ramen noodles.
Stir well and set aside.

title: strawberry pie *
directions: Add juice to milk and stir until thick.
Add berries and extract.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into shell and chill.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Peel carrots and boil until extra soft. Drain well. While carrots are warm, add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Whip with mixer until smooth. Add flour and mix well. Beat eggs and add to carrot mixture. Blend well and add softened butter. Blend well. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Arrange in alternate layers in buttered 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish the macaroni, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour 2 cups milk mixed with beaten eggs over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until golden brown in 350° oven (about 40 minutes).

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and regular sugar.
Push together into pie pan and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool crust.

title: creamy black bean dip
directions: Drain and rinse black beans.
Mash beans with a fork.
Blend in yogurt, chilies, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Chill and serve.

title: chess cake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and one egg.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar (can use 2/3 of box of sugar) and 2 eggs.
Pour over layer in pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and almond until smooth (add 2 tablespoons milk if necessary), then add nuts and raisins.
Serve with apple slices.

title: broiled pompano
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place 2 filets wrapped in foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Squeeze lemon over fish.
Salt lightly and brush with melted butter.
Broil with foil open for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into 6 patties.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch squares.
Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons hot oil in large skillet, stirring until tender-crisp; remove to dish and set aside.
In same skillet, heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil until hot.
Add chicken and stir-fry over high heat until chicken cooks through, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: vidalia onion flower
directions: With sharp knife, carefully peel onion and trim root end, leaving it intact.
Standing onion on its root end, cut parallel slices at 1/4-inch intervals into, but not through, onion, stopping about 1/2 above root end.
Rotate onion 90°; cut parallel vertical slices in same manner to form a crosshatch pattern, keeping onion intact.
Coat microwave-safe pie plate with vegetable cooking spray.
Place onion, root end down in center of pie plate.
Drizzle with margarine and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave at High 3 minutes.
Baste with cooking liquid and rotate dish.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes longer or until onion spreads open into a "flower." Sprinkle with pecans.

title: christmas morning monkey bread
directions: Grease tube or Bundt pan well.
Place 1/3 of the biscuits in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover first layer of biscuits with half of the mixture.
Place the next 1/3 of the biscuits and top with remaining nut mixture.

Place last 1/3 of the biscuits on top and bake 45 to 55 minutes at 300° or until dark golden brown. Immediately invert onto serving platter and cool slightly before serving by "pulling apart" with fingers.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add 6 cups water.
Let mixture come to a boil and then boil 5 minutes.
Cool several hours.
Take mixture and, with an electric mixer, add Cool Whip. Fold in mandarin oranges.
Keep chilled.

title: golden crumbled potatoes
directions: Melt butter or oleo.
Combine cornflakes and seasonings.
Roll potatoes in oleo and then in cornflakes.
Arrange in a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until tender.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Simmer for 5 minutes the jello, crushed pineapple and juice. Cool and add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.

title: e z chicken
directions: Cook broccoli; place in casserole or pan.
Cover with cooked chicken.
Mix mushroom soup, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and curry powder; spread over chicken.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Melt oleo; stir in bread crumbs until covered.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: opra's unfried french fries
directions: Prepare potatoes by sprinkling with the spices.
Next, spray the potatoes with Pam.
Take the egg whites and pour over the seasoned, sprayed potatoes and toss lightly; drain and then place the potatoes on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
With the oven set on 325°, bake until done.

title: mae's salsa
directions: Peel, quarter and core tomatoes.
Chop onions and sweet pepper into 1/2-inch pieces. Dice hot peppers.
Place all ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over low heat until done.
Pour into pint jars and seal.

title: banana custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks.
Pour on scalded milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat in heavy pan, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cool and add lemon juice and banana.
Chill thoroughly.
Spoon into pie shell and cover with meringue.
Bake until lightly browned in 450° oven for about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: never grainy pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt together.
Add eggs, pumpkin and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes; reduce to moderate heat (350°) and continue baking about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in pie mixture comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with cheese, if desired. Makes 1 (9-inch) single crust pie.

title: tennessee pudding cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix soda and milk and allow to stand until doubled.
Add eggs to butter and sugar.
Cream thoroughly.
Add milk and soda.
Add flour and pinch of salt.
Beat until well mixed.
Add dates, nuts and coconut.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Blend in jam.
Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: amber glow
directions: Mold cream cheese into small, plastic margarine tub.
Loosen edges; place in pretty serving dish.
Blend preserves, dry mustard, horseradish and pepper flakes and pour over cream cheese. Sprinkle peanuts over apricot mixture.
Serve with whole wheat crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place all of the ingredients, except the bacon, in a bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour the beans into a baking pan and lay the bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese christmas stollen
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour plus next 3 ingredients.
Stir in oats. Beat butter and sugar until creamy. Add lemon peel.
Beat in egg, egg yolks, cottage cheese and last 1/2 cup of flour.
Stir in raisins, candied fruit and nuts.
Dough will be stiff and biscuit like.
Divide dough in half.
Turn out on lightly floured board. With palms of hands, press each half into oval shape 1/2-inch thick. Fold in 1/2 lengthwise.
Lift to lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool on rack. Decorate with frosting and candied cherries.

title: kernel corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, baking powder, sugar, flour and salt in a mixing bowl. Combine eggs, milk, corn kernels and butter. Add this mixture to the dry ingredients and stir until mixed. Pour into a buttered casserole. Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cereal-raisin treats
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place marshmallows, peanut butter and butter in medium saucepan.
Stirring constantly over low heat, cook 10 to 15 minutes until melted and blended.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in cereal and raisins.
Spread warm mixture in baking pan.
Chill until set.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and flour.
Add vinegar, bouillon and eggs. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Take off heat, strain and add sherry and mix well.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, leaving skins on.
Cut into bite size pieces. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle soup mix over.
Dot with margarine pats (every 1 to 2-inches). Cover with foil. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet-sour tuna
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve liquid.
In
saucepan	combine 1/3 cup of reserved pineapple juice,
water
and green pepper. Cover, simmer 5 minutes.
Add
pineapple.	Combine cornstarch, sweetener, vinegar, soy, bouillon and	boiling
water.
Add to mixture in saucepan.
Cook, stirring
mixture constantly until thick and bubbly.
Add water	chestnuts,
pimiento,
mushrooms and tuna (broken into small pieces).
Simmer
to	3 minutes until heated through.
Serve on	low-calorie
bread,
toasted. Yield:
4 servings.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: In a large pan or crock-pot, melt slowly cranberry sauce, beating with fork.
Slowly add 6 cups water.
Make syrup of 2 cups water, sugar and cloves.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir.
Serve hot.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O and water; dissolve.
Cream the cream cheese. Add pineapple with juice.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with Jell-O.
Chill until congealed.

title: string beans and lamb(or stewed beef)
directions: Brown onion in
oil.
Add 1/4 cup water and lamb meat.
Cook over low heat.
Brown on both sides.
Add tomato paste and remaining water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes.
Add string beans and cook until beans are tender.

title: "easy pineapple cake"
directions: Empty pineapple into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add pie filling on top.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pie filling.
Dot with oleo.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350° for metal pan or at 325° for glass pan.

title: zucchini and pasta medley
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onions, zucchini and squash and saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cook, stirring until tomato paste is dissolved.
Reduce heat to low and continue to cook, stirring occasionally until vegetables are thoroughly cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked linguine.

title: ham and cheese puff
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the first 2 ingredients; mix with bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of bread cubes.
Cover and put in icebox for 6 hours or overnight (best).
Bake without cover.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix baking mix, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and milk.
Set aside. In a 10-inch skillet, combine remaining brown sugar, peaches, cornstarch, butter, ginger and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Drop batter mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot peach mixture.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes; cover and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes until dumplings are fluffy.
To serve, spoon syrup over dumplings and top with whipped cream.
Serves six to eight.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and flour in large mixing bowl until creamy. Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over crust. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean at 350° about 55 minutes. Immediately spread with sour cream topping. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: winnie's date nut loaf candy
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan. Cook until dissolved and add dates, then bring to a boil. Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from flame. Add other ingredients. Beat until cool. Roll in wet soft cloth until firm. Slice.
Nothing better.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line foil lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate; carefully remove foil.
Invert to right side.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with combined marmalade and water; chill. Cut into wedges.

title: grandma's pineapple noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until golden brown.
To serve, cut into squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into well greased casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until dissolved.
Blend cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add remaining ingredients, whipped cream too.
Stir in Jell-O.
Pour into Jell-O ring or bowl and chill several hours.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make roux with oil and flour. Add onions and celery. Cook until onions are wilted. Add water and garlic. Cook in heavy pot, uncovered, over medium heat for 1 hour. Season with peppers. Add shrimp, parsley and fish to mixture. Cook another 15 minutes. Add oysters and let come to boil.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Mix the salad oil and the water.
Add the oil and water to the flour and blend with a fork. This is enough for 2 pie crusts.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion and pepper in bacon grease.
Combine other ingredients.
Crumble bacon and mix in well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Slice onions and saute in butter.
Mix eggs and sour cream; add to onions.
Add Tabasco sauce, salt and white pepper.
Place in uncooked deep dish pie crust.
Put grated Parmesan cheese on top. Bake 20 minutes at 450°; lower heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes.

title: tuna-cheese twist
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Lightly grease the cookie sheet.
Mix tuna, olives, celery, green pepper, onion and 1/4 cup of the soup. Mix baking mix and 1/2 cup cold water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into rectangle 14 x 11 inches; place on cookie sheet.
Spoon the tuna mixture lengthwise down the center of the rectangle; sprinkle with 1 cup of the cheese.
Make cuts 2 1/2 inches long at 1-inch intervals on the sides of the rectangle.
Fold the strips over the filling.
Mix egg with 1 tablespoon of water; brush over the dough.
Bake until light brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix the remaining soup and 1/2 cup cheese and the milk over medium heat, stirring occasionally until hot. Serve over slices of twist.
Serves 6.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and pecans.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Stir in cold water and add cherry pie filling. Chill.
If desired, you can add 1 cup cream (whipped) when Jell-O is partially set.

title: supper-on-a-bread slice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut French bread in
half lengthwise. Spread meat mixture evenly over top
surface
of bread. Wrap heavy-duty Reynolds
aluminum
wrap
around crust side of each 1/2 loaf,
leaving top uncovered.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for
minutes.
Garnish	with strips of cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend until frothy.

title: no-bake breakfast bars
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray.

title: grandma's tea cakes(recipe is over 200 years old)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Pour mixture into 7 cups unsifted flour and work into a stiff dough. Roll thin and cut with a round cookie cutter.
Bake in hot oven at 400° about 8 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Fill an 8 x 8-inch pan with sliced peaches.
Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add egg and work mixture with fingers.
Spread on top of peaches.
Melt margarine and drizzle over.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before removing from pan. Cool completely before icing.
(You can just sprinkle with confectioners sugar.)

title: toscana soup
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Bake Italian sausage on jelly-roll pan 15 to 20 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Cool and cut into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Cook chopped onion and diced bacon in saucepan over medium heat, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in minced garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add chicken broth, water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in fresh kale, whipping cream and sausage.
Cook 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yogurt
directions: Scald milk (do not boil), then let cool until it is very warm, but not hot.
Stir in milk powder.
Gently stir in yogurt.
