Place in a very warm area, covered with a loose lid, and allow to rest for 3 to 5 hours undisturbed.
Yogurt mixture will thicken.
Store well covered in refrigerator.

title: beef chow mein
directions: Saute steak in margarine 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and onion to meat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add celery and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and sprouts.
Mix together cornstarch, soy sauce and molasses.
Add to rest.
Cook low until ready to eat.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Very good in the winter!!

title: charlie's potato tuna chowder
directions: Combine 1 cup potatoes, chicken stock, onion and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce the heat, cover and simmer around 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add sage, paprika and pepper to the saucepan. With a fork, mash the potatoes in a saucepan.
Add remaining potatoes, carrots, green beans, celery and milk to the mashed potatoes in saucepan. Bring to a boil, then immediately reduce the heat.
Simmer for about 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add tuna fish to the saucepan. Simmer for 5 minutes until well heated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread pudding(fat-free)
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk, sugar, egg substitute, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in bread cubes and pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with a no-stick cooking spray.
Place baking dish into a pan of water 1-inch deep. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 4.
Less than 1/2 gram fat per serving.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, eggs, parsley and salt; mix lightly.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in margarine; drain. Place in 2-quart casserole.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix thoroughly the powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter. Roll in small balls and chill overnight.
Melt almond bark and dip candy balls in mixture.
Yields about 60.

title: green beans supreme
directions: In skillet, cook onion and 2 tablespoons butter until onion is transparent. Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once and cook until mixture is thick and bubbly. Remove from heat and add sour cream and then add beans. Spread 1/3 of bean mixture in greased casserole and sprinkle with half the cheese. Repeat layers, ending with beans.

title: rebo's artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Chop pimentos.
Mix all ingredients together.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with chips.

title: microwave cream-style corn
directions: Cut corn from cob, scraping cobs well to remove all milk. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish with 3/4 cup water.
Microwave 8 minutes.
Add sweet milk and cornstarch after blending well together.
Then add salt, pepper and oil.
Microwave another 10 minutes.
Yield: About 6 servings.

title: diabetic chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, cocoa and flour. Cook in a double boiler until thick and smooth. Add Equal. Mix. Pour into pie shell.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the bread crumbs for bottom layer and end with cheese.
Mix in large bowl, eggs, milk and spices; pour over layer of bread.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Dissolve jello with water and add strawberries.
Chill jello just until thickened, then spoon over other ingredients.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place
mixture
of potatoes, onions, chicken soup, sour cream and margarine in large, flat baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add cheese; bake until melted. Serves 12.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger with however much salt and pepper you like.
Add can of Spanish rice and mix together thoroughly.
Put into a loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
You have to keep draining grease.
Pour your own special thick hot sauce over it before serving.

title: angel food pie
directions: Beat
egg
whites
stiff and stir in the sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into buttered and floured pie plate.
Bake in 325° oven
for 40 minutes.
Open door and let the pie cool in the
oven (it
will	fall).	When cool, cover with whipped cream
and grated
unsweetened
chocolate.
Let
cool	in the refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: no-cook chocolate fudge
directions: Cream
cheese
until
soft and smooth.
Blend in sugar. Add melted
chocolate; mix well.
Add vanilla, salt, nuts and mix. Press into well-greased shallow pan and chill until firm (about 15 minutes) or form into small balls and chill.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into long cake pan.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely and frost.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix 3 dry ingredients and add boiling water slowly.
Cool.
Put quart of halved or sliced strawberries in pie shell (I prefer graham cracker crust) and pour mixture over.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip vegetables of choice.

title: corn dog muffins
directions: Combine corn bread mix and brown sugar.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Stir in corn and hot dogs.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups three-fourths full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add grated cheese. Sift flour with dry ingredients and add to butter and cheese mixture.
Beat eggs until light. Add water.
Add to flour mixture to make stiff dough. Chill.
Roll 1/4-inch in thickness. Cut in strips 4-inches long and 1/4-inch in width.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and add to large bowl. Add the red onions and green pepper. In a small bowl, add the salad oil, wine vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt and pepper. Mix until the sugar is dissolved, then add to the beans, stirring to coat the beans thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti with marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl. Marinate at room temperature 30 minutes.
Cook pasta.
Add tomatoes.
Toss and serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2 as a main dish or 4 as a side dish.

title: banana cream pie - best!
directions: Combine
cookie
crumbs with melted butter.
Press into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Chill.
Slice two bananas evenly over crust. Pour instant pudding
over
milk;
beat
one
minute. Stir in vanilla and fold
in whipped cream.
Heap filling into pie shell covering bananas; chill until firm.
To serve, slice remaining banana over top
of
pie
and
sprinkle with chopped nuts.
If you do not wish
to
use nuts, sprinkle a few chocolate crumbs over top of pie.
Serves 8.

title: sweet dough
directions: Mix together the milk, sugar and salt, crumble into mixture the cakes of yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in eggs and shortening.
Mix in first with spoon, then with hand 7 cups flour. Add flour in 2 additions, using amount necessary to make it easy to handle.
When the dough begins to leave the sides of the bowl, turn it onto floured board and knead.
Fold dough over toward you, press down away from you with heel of hand.
Repeat until it's smooth and doesn't stick to board.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down, pull edges into center and let rise again until double in bulk, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: yeast roll recipe
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and egg. Add flour; let rise until double and stir down.
Make into rolls. Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 2 dozen rolls.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain liquid from clams saving it for later.
Add the clams to softened cream cheese.
Add enough of the liquid to make a "dippable" consistency.
Add chiles to taste.
Good with corn chips.

title: pickled herring
directions: Wash herrings thoroughly and soak in cold water for 12 hours, changing water twice.
Remove the head, tail and entrails; save the milt.
Remove the skin and bones.
Rinse the fillets well and drain.
Cut each fillet into 4 to 5 pieces.
Put the milt through a sieve; combine with oil.
Boil vinegar, water, peppercorns and bay leaves for 10 minutes; cool.
Blend with milt mixture; place in jar.
Cover tightly and let stand for 1 day.
Arrange attractively, garnish with chopped parsley or chives.

title: turtle pretzels
directions: In a double boiler, melt caramels and water.
Dip half of each pretzel into the hot caramel.
Place on a greased sheet of foil to cool.
In a saucepan, melt chocolate and shortening over low heat. Dip caramel coated end of pretzels into the chocolate; sprinkle with nuts.
Return to foil.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Mix and bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil. Mix the rest of ingredients. Then add the 2 mixtures together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy potato strips
directions: Put the potato strips in a 2-quart greased baking dish and pour milk over them.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake until the potatoes are tender.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Sprinkle parsley over cheese and let sit until cheese melts.

title: envy salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water in mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese. Beat at medium speed until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients by hand.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into 2 large rolls. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until it starts to thicken.
Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar and add to pudding mixture.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Layer pudding mixture, then crumbled Oreos in large glass bowl (glass looks better).
Alternate layers until gone.
Put Oreos, crumbled, on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, sugar and soda.
Make hole in middle and add bananas, pecans, vanilla, pineapple, oil and eggs.
Mix well but do not beat.
Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corn-sausage chowder
directions: Cook sausage and onions until sausage is brown and onions tender.
Put in pot and add salt, pepper and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are done.
Add corn and milk.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: hush puppy muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Spray small cup muffin tin with nonstick vegetable coating.
Mix dry ingredients, including onion, with a fork.
Make a well in center and pour in the boiling water. Stir briskly.
Stir in beaten egg, margarine and Tabasco.
Spoon 2 tablespoons batter into each muffin cup.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Makes a dozen small muffins.

title: joe's vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3 quart casserole. Cover in cracker crumbs and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil zucchini and sugar for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and crushed pineapple with juice.
Boil 10 minutes.
Stir in dry gelatin and mix well.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.
Keep in refrigerator or freeze.

title: steak stroganoff(crock pot)
directions: Mix flour, garlic powder, and pepper in slow cooker.
Trim beef and cut into 1 inch strips.
Add to flour mixture.
Toss to coat well.
Add mushroom soup, water and soup mix.
Mix well.
Cook on low for 6-7 hours or high for 3-3 1/2 hours.
Stir in mushrooms and sour cream.
Cook on high for 15-20 minutes, or until heated. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Add soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour last. Bake at 300° to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on cookie sheets. Press down on cookies with a wet fork before baking.

title: blazing barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet; cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line a pizza pan or other pan with crescent rolls.
Top with sausage and cheese. Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice and broccoli dish
directions: Add broccoli, rice, soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until slightly brown on top.

title: okra
directions: Bring to boil (3 minutes). Put in jar and seal. When preparing to cook, wash off in cold water. Cover in buttermilk approximately 2 hours. Pour off and roll in corn meal. Fry.

title: potluck casserole with corn bread crust
directions: Heat Wesson oil in frypan.
Crumble ground beef into frypan and brown, stirring frequently.
Add cabbage, carrots, onion, green pepper, celery, salt and hot water.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour mixture into 4-quart casserole.
Add soup and 1/2 soup can of water.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Place in casserole dish as listed.
Salt and pepper to taste as you add layers. Cook, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.

title: venison-veggi bundles
directions: Dice vegetables and mix together.
Season with tarragon.
Lay each steak on a square of heavy aluminum foil.
Place a heaping spoonful of vegetables on top of each steak.
Seal foil around steak and vegetables.
Cook over hot coals for approximately 1 hour.

title: lazy wife's cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan. Add sugar, milk and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into oblong cake pan.
Put pie filling on top and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter on medium speed until light.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
After mixture becomes light, add Cool Whip, a little at a time.
(Cool Whip should be thawed.)
Spoon into crust.
Freeze for 8 hours.

title: crab dip
directions: In bowl, blend all ingredients.
Cover; chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: veggie dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serve with veggie tray.

title: micro peanut brittle
directions: Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir well.
Cook 4 more minutes. Stir well.
Add vinegar and oleo.
Stir and cook 2 minutes more. Take out and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir gently, but well.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 30 minutes.
Break into pieces and store in Tupperware.

title: marble cheese cake
directions: To make crust, combine flour, sugar, salt and oleo until it is a fine crumb mixture.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of melted chocolate bits.
Press on bottom of a 9 inch spring form pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Even makes a good dessert.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: broccoli slaw(vegetarian)
directions: In bowl, mix broccoli slaw, sunflower seeds, sliced almonds and uncooked Ruma noodles. In small bowl, mix the oil, vinegar and sugar or substitute. Stir to dissolve the sugar. Add both mixtures together just before serving.

title: dollie's indian tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar together in a mixing bowl.
Next cut in butter, then add buttermilk, egg and vanilla.
Roll thin, cut in desired shape and bake on a greased cookie sheet in a hot oven.
Watch closely to avoid overcooking.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Mix together dressing mix, oil, water and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken breast and marinate for at least 1 hour.
Remove chicken from marinade and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice of Mozzarella over chicken breast.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Cut bacon in 1/2-inch pieces and fry to a very light brown; add onion and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thickened.
Serve hot.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: celery casserole
directions: Melt butter; put 1/2 in baking dish.
Boil celery for 5 minutes in salt water.
Drain and put in baking dish.
Place sliced chestnuts on top of celery.
Pour soup over.
Crunch crackers on top of soup, then almonds and butter on top.
Bake in 7 x 10-inch baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate using baking chocolate.
Mix chocolate or cocoa, baking soda, 1/3 cup oil and water.
Stir until thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and rest of oil until smooth.
Add vanilla, flour and salt; blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: egg foo yong and sauce
directions: Beat eggs and water until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients. Fry in hot oil using 1/4 cup egg mixture for each.
Keep warm in covered dish in oven.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in saucepan and heat to boil.
Stir well while at full boil for 5 minutes.
Pour this hot mixture over remaining ingredients that have been broken into small pieces. Stir until everything is melted.
Pour out into greased pans.

title: pork chops italian style
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops in shallow baking pan (little water on bottom of pan).
Brown until almost done, turning once.
Remove from oven and place 1/2 piece cheese on each chop and spoon on tomato sauce.
Return to oven and cook until cheese is melted and heated through.

title: blackfoot potato soup with sausage
directions: In a Dutch oven or heavy kettle, brown sausage over medium heat. Remove sausage with slotted spoon and reserve. Drain any excess fat. Add celery, onion, thyme and salt; cook until onion is tender. Stir in flour; cook 1 minute. Gradually add chicken broth and water. Cook, stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Add potatoes. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Pour 2 cups soup mixture into container of electric blender; process until smooth. Return to kettle. Add milk, beans and reserved sausage; heat. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas or enchiladas de pollo
directions: Boil or saute 3 chicken breasts (cut into chunks); saute onion. Drain extra butter from chicken and onions.
Lay tortillas out flat.
Place chicken, onion, cream cheese and Monterey Jack cheese and chilies, making sure you have enough for 12 tortillas.
Place tortillas in a pan; cover them with Monterey Jack cheese.
Pour cream over all tortillas.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Very good!

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; add beans and all other ingredients. Bake uncovered until beans are brown and bubbly (45 minutes) at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes, then uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons oleo in top of double boiler.
Add the flour and mix well.
Add milk and chicken broth and beat with wire whip until smooth.
Saute onion in 4 tablespoons oleo for 3 minutes, then add to mix.
Cook for 15 minutes (do not boil).
Add salt, pepper, green onions and cream.
Serve.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash and add cream, cream cheese, butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes until heated through and lightly brown on top.
You can make up a week before ready to use. Keep in refrigerator until ready to bake.
(This is good to fix ahead for company.)

title: cherry cream freeze
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Gently fold in whipped cream until evenly blended.
Turn mixture into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Freeze 24 hours or until thoroughly firm.
Unmold on to serving tray.

title: ground beef spinach wheel
directions: Brown meat in large frypan.
Drain.
Add packaged spinach. Cover and cook until thawed.
Stir in pepper and salt or soy sauce, soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Turn mixture into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cut cheese into thin, 1/2 x 3-inch strips and arrange on top to resemble wheel spokes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese melts and crumbs brown.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Roll eggplant in egg, then Italian bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil on both sides.
Place into 8 x 10-inch baking dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together about 2 minutes.
Pour slowly over eggs, stirring well.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until done.
Pie will be done when completely puffed across top.

title: savory glazed meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine meat, water chestnuts, eggs, bread crumbs and bouillon.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch meatballs. In large skillet, brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet; discard fat.
In same skillet, combine remaining ingredients. Over low heat, cook and stir 5 minutes.
Add meatballs; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Ummmm - good!

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Add onion and sour cream to drained noodles.
Place in casserole; sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lemon drops
directions: Cream butter to soften; then thoroughly cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, lemon peel and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add alternately with lemon juice. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with tinted sugar.
Bake in moderate oven set at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp, corn and crab chowder
directions: Pour heavy whipping cream in pot. Add water and 2 tablespoons crab boil. Let come to a boil, then place on low heat. Add cream of celery soup. Use wire whisk and blend into cream mixture. Add frozen corn. Saut green onions, shrimp and crab meat in a small amount of olive oil. Pour into soup mixture. You may add crab boil to taste. Simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: georgia tea cakes
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar and flour. Mix well. Add vanilla, ice water and nutmeats. Knead well with hands until well blended. Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness. Bake in moderate oven. When done and still hot, sift powdered sugar on each. Store in tin box. Do not handle too much.

title: frozen orange yogurt
directions: In a small saucepan, combine gelatin and water; let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Heat and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Cool. In a large bowl, combine orange juice concentrate, yogurt, Equal and vanilla; stir in gelatin mixture.
Pour into a 4-quart ice cream freezer; freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Makes about 2 quarts.
Diabetic food exchanges, 1/2 milk, 1/2 fruit and 1/2 fat.

title: cherry pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix the cornstarch, sugar and salt in a pan.
Add cherry juice slowly to make a smooth paste, and then add remainder of juice.
Cook while stirring until the mixture begins to bubble. Remove from fire and stir in butter and add cherries.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Apply top pie crust and bake at 425 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees for 15 - 25 minutes longer.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Chill until serving time. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over macaroni mixture.
Toss to mix.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cookies made by kids(with parents help!)
directions: You may add jimmy candy to batter for funfetti effect (about 1/4 cup).

title: heavenly chocolate berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in melted chocolate chips.
When well beaten, fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into crust and chill at least 8 hours.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry or cherry jello in 1 cup boiling water; partially cool. Stir in cherry pie filling. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate covered coconut balls
directions: Mix coconut, Eagle Brand milk and sugar in large bowl.
Form into small balls.
Use 1/4 cup powdered sugar to dust your hands before forming balls.
Lay balls on wax paper to dry.
Melt the chocolate chips and wax in pan.
Dip coconut balls in melted chocolate to coat.
Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oatmeal, brown sugar, shortening and salt.
Cover with boiling water and let stand.
Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup water and add sugar.
Pour into oatmeal.
Add flour and knead for 5 minutes. Put into greased bowl and let rise until double, about 1 hour. Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Form 2 loaves and put in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double, about 45 minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian delight cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients until smooth.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom of small aluminum lined cups.
Put a tablespoon of filling on top of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Put spoonful of cherry pie filling on top of each cookie. Refrigerate.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together well with mixer.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake approximately 45 minutes.

title: candy mints to enjoy
directions: Blend milk into sugar.
Divide mixture.
Tint one pink and one green.
Roll balls.
Put on waxed paper.
Flatten each ball with thumb.
Decorate with pecans on top.
Other colors and extracts can be used.

title: healthful homemade nuggets
directions: Marinate chicken pieces in olive oil, garlic and pepper for approximately 30 minutes.
Pour off marinade.
Mix bread crumbs with cayenne.
Lightly dredge chicken pieces in mixture.
Spread in a single layer on a cookie sheet and bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Run under broiler for extra browning.
Serve warm with a dip of honey mustard, barbecue or sweet and sour sauce.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs, beating well after each addition.
When mixture becomes stiff, add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into gallon freezer.
Freeze as directed by your freezer.

title: quick no-fail fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute; then beat with a hand mixer until thick.
Spread into a buttered pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips.
Put in shallow dish. Spread crushed chips on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook until boiling for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Place on wax paper with spoon.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all and put cheese on top.
Cover.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Put onion rings on and bake uncovered 10 minutes longer.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix the water and Jell-O. Cool.
To the cake mix, add the oil and mix well. Add the eggs and beat. Add the lemon extract.
Mix in the cool Jell-O.
Bake in greased pan approximately 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and punch holes from top to bottom with a meat fork.
Pour over the cake a mixture of the lemon juice and confectioners sugar.
Serve warm or cool. Also good topped with whipped cream.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Combine rest of ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over vegetables and let set overnight at least.
Mixture will keep several weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic until softened.
Add the cubed chicken and brown; drain the fat and add the mushrooms.
Mix together with the cooked noodles and then add the remaining ingredients except the cheese and Durkee onions.
Mix thoroughly and spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly; top with cheese and Durkee onions.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, salad oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: succotash(low-fat)
directions: Mix Butter Buds into the skim milk and set aside.
Heat the oil over low heat in heavy saucepan and saute onion until soft. Add corn, salt and milk mixture and simmer 3 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Add lima beans.
Cover and simmer gently until beans are heated through, about 3 minutes.

title: snow peaks
directions: Scald diluted evaporated milk in double boiler.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and beaten egg yolks. Add to milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Remove at once; cool and add wine.
Pour custard into sherbet glasses. Add peaches and top with meringue made by beating egg whites with confectioners sugar and almond extract.
Serves 6.

title: no bake peanut butter fudge cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a pan;
bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add quickly the oats, salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Drop onto cookie sheet covered with waxed paper or foil.
Refrigerate until hardened.

title: zesty ham spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve on crackers or miniature rolls (I call tea biscuits).

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Slightly thaw hash browns.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with non-stick coating.
Melt velveeta in microwave, stirring every two minutes.
When melted, stir in mayonnaise until blended.
Pour over hash browns.
Cover and bake about 45 minutes at 300°.
Uncover and bake about 10 to 15 more minutes until slightly brown and bubbly.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces; season.
Pound flour into one side. Combine remaining ingredients with just enough water to moisten. Place small amount of stuffing on each steak on unfloured side. Roll up and tie with string.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water. Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and chocolate.

title: heavenly seven layered salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.

title: mama's starlight cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade spaghetti supper
directions: Brown ground beef in electric skillet and drain fat.
Return to skillet and add all other ingredients, except the spaghetti. Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce to simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: james' meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In a shallow pan, shape into loaf.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Stud each peach with 3 or 4 cloves.
Pack into a quart jar. Simmer remaining ingredients for 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Slip the cinnamon stick in, too.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: diabetic milk shake
directions: Blend ice cream, milk and jello.
Do not dissolve in water. While blending the mixture, add 4 to 6 ice cubes until thick.

title: *pastichio 1(macaroni and meat)
directions: Boil macaroni.
Saute onion in some butter.
Add hamburg, salt and pepper.
Cook until done.
Butter 10 x 14-inch pan.
Line the roasting pan with 4 sheets of phyllo, buttering each sheet.
Add 1/3 of the macaroni, 1/3 of the hamburg and a layer of cheese. Continue the layers, ending with the macaroni.

title: hot tomato sipper
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes or until bouillon dissolves.
Serve hot. Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Clean and cook carrots; cut lengthwise into 3/8-inch strips. Cook and stir brown sugar, salt and orange peel in margarine in 12-inch skillet until bubbly.
Add carrots; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed and heated through, about 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings; 110 calories per serving.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf, basting occasionally for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green pepper, onion, pineapple, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill for several hours and serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: excellent lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cream cornstarch, 1 1/4 cups sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat egg yolks and add to cream cornstarch mixture.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix soup, water, celery, onion and stuffing.
Spoon into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Place chicken on stuffing mixture. Mix margarine, sugar and mustard; spread over chicken.

title: black bean and corn chili over baked potatoes
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil in a medium-sized saucepan over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes or until the onion is translucent.
Add the beans, tomatoes and their liquid, tomato paste, corn, chili powder, cumin and sugar and stir to combine. Reduce the heat.
Cover the pan and simmer the mixture 15 to 20 minutes.
Add the bell pepper and cook the chili another 5 minutes.
Ladle the chili over 4 baked potatoes and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; slice squash thin and add it with corn. Cover and steam until squash is tender; add cheese.
Pour into casserole dish; top with crushed Fritos.
Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat hot potatoes until all lumps are removed.
Add cream cheese (in small pieces) and the butter.
Beat well until cheese and butter are completely melted and mixed. Stir in sour cream.
To the milk add the eggs and onion.
Add to the potato mixture along with salt and pepper.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Place in a greased 9 inch round casserole. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
This recipe is delicious left over.

title: vegen fajitas
directions: Dice onions, garlic and green onion.
Slice bell pepper, tomatoes and summer squash.
Saute in skillet, adding cumin, salt, pepper, tomatoes and cilantro in last.
Saute for 15 minutes. Serve in flour or corn tortillas with sour cream and hot sauce.

title: jacob's gang favorite million dollar fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl, place chopped nuts, chocolate chips, chocolate bar pieces, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
In a saucepan, place sugar and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over contents in bowl.
Stir until melted, then pour into buttered pans.
When set, cut into squares.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix cream cheese with chicken soup.
Add diced chicken.
Take crescent dinner rolls and pull apart.
Stretch each section and fill with mixture.
Roll up ends.
Roll in melted butter and crushed herb croutons or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into French fry strips.
Put potatoes in a shallow pan lined with aluminum foil.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Add cream.
Fold foil over top and seal by pinching together. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: spinach salad with strawberries and almonds and sesame seed
directions: Spray baking sheet with cooking spray.
Sprinkle sesame seed over sheet.
Turn on oven to 350° and remove 10 minutes later. Combine sesame seed in a jar with all other ingredients.
Shake well; check for seasoning and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine melted margarine, beaten eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie shells.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 45 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt in saucepan (I use a number 8 large skillet).
Do not stir after sugar is dissolved.
Cook until boiling syrup, when dropped from spoon in cold water, forms a hard, almost brittle ball (265° by thermometer).
Remove from fire.

title: orange julius
directions: In a blender, mix on high speed the juice, Dream Whip, vanilla and pudding.
Add a few ice cubes and continue to blend.
Serve chilled.
Enjoy!

title: rice and peppers
directions: Put the rice into greased casserole dish.
Saute green pepper and onion in fat until browned.
Add catsup, tomato juice and seasoning, mix well.
Pour over rice and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.

title: burgundy onions
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices.
This should be about 2-quarts. Separate the slices into rings.
Heat butter in skillet. Add onions, tossing them about with a wooden spoon until rings are coated with butter.
Add cloves and salt. Continue to cook over low heat until onions just start to brown. Add wine. Cover pan and simmer about 15 minutes.
Onions should be slightly crisp but tender.
Remove cover and cook until wine is reduced to a glaze. Serve at once. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet, saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Place chicken breasts over vegetables.
In a bowl, combine tomato sauce, chilies and seasonings.
Pour over chicken; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and is tender.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: reuben dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in a small saucepan over low heat.
Thin with more milk if necessary.
Serve with cocktail rye bread.
Also works good in a crock-pot.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in pan. Add noodles until slightly browned, stirring well. Add rice to mixture. Saut together for a few minutes, stirring well. Add broth, water and salt. Bring to a boil for a few minutes. Stir and cover. Cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Let rest 5 to 10 minutes. Serve cold.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain grease from sausage (this part is optional, I want to get rid of the grease.)
After sausage has been drained, add jar of Cheez Whiz.
When mixed well and melted, put on half of English muffin.
All muffins need to be opened and in halves.
Spoon mixture on top of each half.
Put on broil and lightly brown.
May be frozen before you brown.
Then just take out as needed and brown.

title: malibu cooler
directions: In blender, combine juice, extracts and ice cubes; blend until ice is coarsely chopped, about 1 minute.
Pour into chilled 16 ounce glass.
Stir in soda.
Calories: 54.

title: holiday franks
directions: Grind up hot peppers, a little cabbage, green tomatoes, carrots, etc.
Put in a big pan to heat on oven.
Mix 1/2 vinegar and 1/2 water mixture and sugar.
Pour over pepper mixture.
Do not cover completely.
Heat to boil.
Pack in jars and cold pack for 20 minutes or pressure can for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix the Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip, then add the other ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Break Oreo cookies in half.
Place
of
cookies in oblong dish.
Prepare chocolate
pudding
according
to directions on box.
Spoon 1/2 of
pudding
over cookies; add 1/2 of Cool Whip. Layer rest of cookies, pudding and Cool Whip.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Sift cake flour then measure 1 c.
Sift sugar then measure.
Sift 1/2 c. sugar, cake flour, and salt together.
Sift 5 times.
Fold into egg white alternating with 1 c. sifted sugar. Add vanilla and bake.
Bake at 325° for 40-45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cover shrimp with salted water to which caraway seed has been added.
Cook slowly 15 to 20 minutes for large and 10 to 12 minutes medium shrimp.
Mix 1/3 cup of butter.
Add onion and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste.
Combine 2 cups tomato juice and salt.
Add 3 tablespoons cornstarch, dissolved in 1/2 cup of juice, celery salt and garlic salt.
Cook 15 minutes in covered saucepan.
Add mushrooms, green pepper, shrimp and baking soda.
Simmer several minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Stir dry gelatin into Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
Stir well together and cover.
Let stand
in the refrigerator a few hours or overnight.

title: baked salmon patties
directions: In medium bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Shape into patties; place in lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until firm.
Makes 3 servings.
May double recipe.

title: two-minute fudge
directions: Mix well sugar, cocoa, corn syrup and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until ready to spread in buttered dish.
Cut into squares.

title: orange yogurt loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
In another bowl, combine melted butter (cooled), eggs, orange rind and orange juice.
Blend thoroughly.
Beat liquid into dry ingredients alternately with yogurt; mix until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or until loaf is golden and pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.
Blend powdered sugar with enough orange juice to make icing to spoon over loaf.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach well. Pat dry with paper towels. Mix all ingredients; chill. Let set out to soften a few minutes before serving. Garnish with Parmesan cheese. Serve with veggies or white corn chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, vanilla, sugar and peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: pecan candy
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Wheat Thin crackers, forming a sandwich.
Roll these in melted chocolate bark and let dry on waxed paper.
Store in covered container.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Place rolls in buttered Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pudding.
Pour melted oleo over top.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Top with nuts.
Cover loosely with foil and a towel and let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan on plate.

title: baked apple donuts
directions: While hot, melt butter.
Put sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Roll hot muffins in butter, then roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Put into a large baking dish.
Top with cheese and potato chips. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls.
Cook at 375 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pan-coat
directions: Put in jar and blend until smooth.
Store in fridge and set out a few minutes before using.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix in pan on stove and warm until mixed well.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients.
Pour over mushrooms.
Chill 24 hours.

title: kringla
directions: Beat egg lightly.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add sour cream.
Mix together baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Sift dry ingredients and slowly add to batter.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Add milk.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add the margarine and milk mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well with mixer.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Knead enough to hold together; roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and fold into halves. Set aside and let rise approximately 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 30 to 40.

title: pasta italiano bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions, pepper and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine noodles and parsley; toss lightly. Combine salad dressing, 1/2 cup cheese and eggs; mix well.
Layer noodle mixture, salad dressing mixture and meat mixture in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in deep pie pan or baking dish.
Then mix together remaining ingredients, except fruit.
Pour this mixture into margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour in canned/sweetened fruit or use fresh fruit and juice which has been cooked.
Do not stir. Bake in moderate oven.
This forms its own crust.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chili powder.
Roll into a small long roll, about the size of a round cracker.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Chill and slice.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend Crisco into flour and salt until quite crumbly.
Add hot water and mix lightly with fork.
Roll out and put in pie tin. Makes 2 crusts.
Very flaky.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix crumbs, milk, beef, salt and pepper well. Make into meatballs and place in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb wine
directions: Add water to rhubarb.
Cover and set aside for 3 days.
Strain. To liquid, add sugar, oranges, lemons, potato and yeast.
Cover and set aside for 14 days.
Strain.
Transfer to tight sealed container.
Ready to drink in 2 to 3 months.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: In a container, with a cover, combine all of the ingredients. Shake or stir until thoroughly combined.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Scramble ground beef,
then
saute
the peppers, onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add
tomatoes
and let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour
over
cooked
spaghetti.
Add a salad and garlic bread and you have a full meal.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients together until potatoes are tender. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thoroughly heated. Serve with corn bread muffins or corn bread sticks.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: shrimp casserole(microwave)
directions: Stir together; cook in microwave for 15 minutes on High; stir on High and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: fruity pebble treats
directions: Melt butter in microwave for about 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows, toss to coat with butter.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 45 seconds.
Immediately add cereal.
Mix until well coated.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: beth's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, sugar, coconut and pecans.
Roll into balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and parafin.
Dip one ball at a time in chocolate mixture and let set on waxed paper.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In a large bowl stir together flour, cocoa powder, salt, baking powder and soda.
In mixer bowl beat together butter and sugar on low speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; beat until well blended.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press down center of dough with thumb.
Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Place cherry in center of each cookie.
In small saucepan combine chocolate pieces and sweetened milk; heat until chocolate is melted.
Stir in 4 teaspoons cherry juice.
Frosting can be thinned by adding more cherry juice.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; cover. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish (9 x 13-inch).

title: maple nut cream pie
directions: In a small saucepan, bring syrup to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add to syrup; mix well.
Beat egg yolks well and add to syrup.
Set aside to cool.
Stir occasionally and when it starts to set, fold in the cream that has been whipped.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground meat until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: cheese straws
directions: Rub margarine into flour.
Add grated cheese, mustard, pepper and enough egg yolk to bind dough which can be rolled out. Sprinkle flour on rolling sheet.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into straws about 1/2-inch wide.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve when cool.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: In ungreased baking dish, pour frozen hash browns.
Mix can of mushroom soup with 1 cup milk and pour over potatoes.
Grate onion and mix with potatoes.
Add salt and pepper, mixing well.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes, making sure potatoes are covered well.
Add grated cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: coffee el greco
directions: Prepare Spice Base by thoroughly creaming butter with brown sugar, spices and salt.
This Spice Base is enough for about 24 servings and may be kept indefinitely in covered container in refrigerator.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
In a different bowl, mix milk or milk substitute with bran.
Let stand until most of the moisture is absorbed.
Add oil, sugar and beaten egg to bran mixture and stir until mixed.
Pour into well-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili rellenos crescent triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small mixing bowl, stir together green chilies and cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and divide into 8 triangles.
Carefully place green chili/cheese filling in center of each triangle, dividing evenly among the 8 triangles.
Fold the triangle carefully to make a smaller version of the same triangle. Seal all edges with fork.
Place on large baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 triangles.

title: eggplant ratatouille
directions: Put
vegetables
in layers; let the tomatoes be on top. Pour the oil over.
Sprinkle Parmesan over the top.
Place in oven at 350°
for
45 minutes.
Good with meat or any kind of salad.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine vegetables, water and seasonings in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until tender. Gradually stir in 1/4 cup milk with 1/4 cup flour, then add rest of milk and Velveeta cheese.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, but do not let it boil!

title: depression plant(not to be eaten)
directions: Put coal in glass dish, about 8-inches in diameter.
Pour remaining ingredients over coal.
Do not stir or move the dish around.
Dot the coal with the ink or food coloring.

Within a few hours your coal will be covered with beautiful growths that somewhat resemble coral and will greatly change from day to day. This is very interesting to watch as it grows so much faster than other plants.
It never fails.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine over medium heat until clear and tender.
Grease a 2-quart casserole (8 x 11 x 2-inch).
Reserve 3 tablespoons of cracker crumbs for topping and line dish with remaining crumbs.
Add onion and soup in alternate layers until dish is full.
cover the top with beaten eggs and pour milk over. Sprinkle on grated cheese and reserved cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: crab sandwich fondue
directions: Mix celery, crab, mayonnaise, etc. together in salad form.
Lay 8 slices of bread in a large buttered pan.
Divide crab mixture evenly; spread on bread.
Top with cheese slice, then top with other slice of bread.
Pour the egg and milk mixture over sandwich. Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with poultry seasoning.
Cut sliced onions on top and around chicken.
Spoon mushroom soup on pieces of chicken.
Salt to taste.
Add water. Cover with foil and cook about an hour in a 350° oven.
Remove foil, break up biscuits in small pieces and drop into liquid, making sure each piece is dipped completely into it.
Return to oven until biscuits brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar; add milk, nuts, eggs and nutmeg. Pour into greased baking dish; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: sauce for over warm cake
directions: Put sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Pour the boiling water in and put on stove.
Bring mixture to a boil and boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: cracker treat
directions: Cover entire cookie sheet with foil.
Line cookie sheet with crackers.
Melt butter in small saucepan; add brown sugar and bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and pour mixture over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle on real chocolate chips and let melt a little.
Spread evenly and refrigerate until chocolate is set.
Break apart into random pieces and serve.

title: chicken - shanghai style
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan and bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to give all pieces an equal turn in the liquid.
After 20 minutes of cooking, remove the cover and increase the heat slightly and continue cooking for about 15 more minutes.
This is when the magic begins; because of the sugar in the liquid.
It will begin to thicken into a beautiful rich brown glaze coating each piece with incredible goodness!
Toss and stir to coat each piece with sauce as it thickens.
Serve with Chicken Rice-A-Roni.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a food processor, turning off and on a few times, until mixed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown, turning once, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices. Dip tomato slices in milk. Coat both sides of tomato in cornmeal mixture.
Lightly shake off excess.
Heat margarine or olive oil on medium to high heat. Fry tomatoes on both sides until golden brown.
Place on plate with paper towel.

title: ma's rolls
directions: Scald milk and let cool. Dissolve sugar, salt and yeast in milk. Add cooking oil and 1/2 flour to milk mixture. Beat until smooth. Work in remaining flour and knead 5 minutes. Set in warm place for 1 hour to rise. Punch dough down. Shape rolls in favorite roll shape. Let rise 5 minutes. Bake at 400°.

title: margaret's gourmet spaghetti and sauce
directions: Boil spaghetti as package instructs, letting your water come to a boil before putting the spaghetti in.
Let spaghetti boil about 10 minutes and add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Boil 5 more minutes; drain and add 2 more tablespoons of butter or margarine while spaghetti is cooking.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into an oblong baking dish. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and heat in microwave until cheese melts and bubbly hot.

title: champagne punch
directions: The day before you plan to serve the punch, freeze the 2 quarts of lemonade in one or two Bundt pans or ring molds.
(It is sometimes helpful to have a back-up ring in the freezer to add during the course of the party.)

title: sweet and spicy mustard dip for chicken fingers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl and microwave on high for 30 seconds, stirring once.
Serve with fried chicken fingers.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in water with bouillon cube.
Add can of soup.
Bring to boil and add rice and chicken.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with more cheese, if desired.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with aluminum foil.
Spray with nonstick spray; set aside.
Spray sides of 3-quart heavy saucepan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat to boiling.
Carefully clip a candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat to 234° (soft ball stage) about 15 minutes, scraping bottom of pan as you stir.
Remove pan from heat; remove thermometer. Add butterscotch pieces, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Stir in 1 cup pecans.
Pour into prepared baking pan, spreading evenly.
If desired, while fudge is still warm, sprinkle with remaining nuts and butterscotch pieces; press gently into top.
Cool in pan.
Cover and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Remove fudge and foil from pan.
Cut into 1 inch squares. Store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Makes 4 1/2 pounds (117 pieces).

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Place jello in refrigerator
and let thicken, then take out and add cottage
cheese,
pineapple,
nuts, mayonnaise and salt. Grease an 8-inch
mold with mayonnaise and add ingredients.
Let stand until set.

title: granny's fruit salad
directions: In a double boiler over medium heat, cook and stir eggs, sugar and vinegar until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat, stir in butter.
Cool.
In a large serving bowl, combine grapes, marshmallows, pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Add cooled dressing and stir to coat.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, fold in whipped cream and pecans.

title: herb and garlic cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer. Store cheese in refrigerator. Serve with crackers.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in medium saucepan until thick (like cooked cereal).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, then eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour to form a soft dough.
Knead well on lightly floured surface.

title: lasagna milanese
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Thaw and drain spinach.
In medium size frying pan brown onion and garlic slightly in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add ground beef. Cook until brown.
Stir in mushrooms including the liquid, tomato paste, bay leaf, 1 teaspoon of salt and oregano.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs in bowl; pour over noodles that are rinsed with cold water. Mix well.	Beat second egg inn bowl.
Add spinach, 1 tablespoon oil, parsley, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, 1 teaspoon salt and basil.
Mix well. Pour 1/2 tomato mixture into oblong shallow dish.
Layer 1/2 noodles on sauce.
Spread the spinach mix.	Repeat noodle layer. Top with rest of tomato mix. Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Remove from oven. Arrange strips of cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted (5 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato, corn & kale chowder
directions: In a large pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Saute carrots, onion, celery, pepper and sweet potato for 3 minutes.
Add thyme, turmeric and combine will with the vegetables.
Add tomato and water or stock, simmer 20 minutes.
Add corn, kale, tofu (if used), salt, pepper and simmer 5 minutes.
Season to taste with cayenne pepper.
Combine cornstarch with 2 tsp cold water.
With soup simmering, stir in the cornstarch mixture.
Continue to stir and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley.
Serve over cooked rice.
This makes a very thick stew.
For a more soup like consistency, add more broth.

title: souper meat 'n potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 of soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasoning.
Press in 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes and top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or more.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over shortening in bowl, stirring until melted.
Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add to shortening mixture with eggs and enough flour to make soft dough. Let rise, covered, in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours to 1 week.

title: artichoke-feta green salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir with a whisk. Stir in artichokes; marinate in the refrigerator 1 hour. Add salad greens, tomatoes and onion. Toss gently. Place 1 1/4 cups salad on each of 4 plates. Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon cheese.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mash everything together.
Make patty and fry.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: First on cookie sheet, arrange graham cracker squares and sprinkle walnuts on them.
Set aside.
Put butter, margarine and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes, checking so they don't burn.
Real good snack.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugars and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Put in a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan before removing.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Day before:
In saucepan, cook chicken in 1 can of chicken broth and water for 30 minutes.
Cut meat from bones in strips. Refrigerate meat and broth.

title: peanut butter cheerio bars
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar over medium heat on stovetop, stirring occasionally, until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat and combine with peanut butter and Cheerios.

title: darrell's chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly after coming to a boil for 6 to 8 hours.

title: sauerkraut ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate overnight.
Good with bland casserole or pork.

title: french toast
directions: Mix egg and milk with fork. Place bread in mix, getting both sides moist. Place on preheated griddle. Let cook for 1 to 2 minutes and turn. Repeat until both sides are golden brown. Top as desired. Makes about 8 to 10 pieces.

title: chick-a-roni
directions: Brown chicken in electric skillet with small amount of oil. Add tomatoes, green pepper, diced onion, salt and pepper.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni (chicken flavor) as directed on box.
Pour chicken mixture over Rice-A-Roni.

title: frozen peanut butter delights
directions: Put peanut butter into mixing bowl.
Slowly add milk while mixing at low speed with electric mixer.
Add the half box of pudding mix.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Let the mixture set up for 5 minutes.
Spread filling 1/2-inch thick on graham cracker squares and cover with a second square.
Freeze until firm, approximately 3 hours.
It can also be used with gingersnap cookies to make the sandwiches.

title: fish sticks
directions: Go to Bi Lo and buy a package of fish sticks.
Put it in the freezer.
Every morning, take 4 out and put in a real small frying pan and put plate on top.
Cook for 20 minutes and turn over. Leave plate off a bit, then take out, put ketchup on them, eat them, then read the paper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter with the dry ingredients, except soda.
Add the sour milk with the soda.
Stir well and pour into buttered and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth, then add all the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into crab shells.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and bake in a hot 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice dish
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add rice.
In a bowl mix mushroom soup, beef consomme soup and water.
Add a little Worcestershire sauce and pepper (no salt).
Put rice in an oblong dish; add liquid and bake 1 hour at 325° or in microwave for 20 minutes on High power, stirring occasionally.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Layer sausage and hash browns.
Pour mixture of eggs and milk over.
Top with grated cheese.
Optional:
Can add onions and red and green peppers.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
If using frozen hash browns, thaw first.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9-inch pie pan with vegetable spray.
Place all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend 2 minutes in blender or bowl.
Pour in pie pan and bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
To serve, cut into 8 pieces.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add 4 tablespoons of melted butter.
Add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Batter is heavy.
Add 2 or 3 diced apples and nuts.
Put in a 9-inch round baking dish or pan. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping. (I cut pieces like a pie.)

title: oven chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Put into baking dish. Add vegetables, soup and spices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: coffee carnival
directions: Add tapioca and salt to
coffee
in double boiler.
Cook 15 minutes or until tapioca is clear, stirring frequently.
Add sugar, chill.
Add vanilla.
Fold
in
whipped cream.
Serve in sherbet glasses.

title: egg brunch
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix bread, meat, cheese and veggies together and put in dish.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Melt oleo and pour over mixture. Cover with foil and refrigerate 6 to 7 hours or overnight.

title: never fail icing
directions: Place egg white, sugar and water in top of double boiler. Place in boiling water.
Keep boiling.
Beat constantly for 7 minutes.
Add flavoring. This is ready to use at once.
If desired, add 1 cup of marshmallows, cut up in frosting before spreading.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Coat Dutch oven with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and onions, saute until tender.
Stir in margarine and flour, cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and stir until blended.
Stir in bouillon, water, garlic powder, parsley and bay leaf.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until slightly thickened.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: danish pastry
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients alone and put in drip pan, then add 1 cup water in pan and 1/2 cup oleo.	Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup flour.	Beat like cream puffs.	Add eggs, one at a time, then add
vanilla.
Bake
hour
Frost with powdered sugar and put nuts on top.

title: rum bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: gary's barbecue sauce
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Makes a gallon of sauce.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Cream applesauce and sugars with butter.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over green beans, celery, bell pepper, onion and peas.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain excess fat (leave some). Sprinkle flour over meat and stir.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until desired consistency. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: nacho cheese chowder
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, crumble the beef.
Add green pepper, cover and microwave on High for 2 1/2 or 3 1/2 minutes, until no pink in meat, stirring once.
Drain fat.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Wash chicken under hot water and pat dry. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix egg whites, salt and cornstarch. Add chicken and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate 45 minutes.
(You can do this part in advance.)

Heat oil in wok. Add chicken and quickly stir-fry. Cook for 3 minutes. With slotted spoon, remove chicken to plate. Reserve 2 tablespoons of oil and pour into clean pan on high heat. Add cashews and onions.
Cook for
1 minute. Add wine/sherry, soy sauce and chicken to pan. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add snow peas and cook 1 minute. Serve over rice.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix chicken, soups, chilies, and sour cream together. Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with vegetable oil, then make layers starting with tortillas, then 1/2 soup mix, then 1/2 cheese. Make 2 layers ending with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: no bake pecan pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add Cool Whip and spread into crust.
Mix pudding and milk together until thick.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture; top with remaining 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: simply sinful casserole
directions: Mix soups, margarine and milk together in a large pot.
Add Velveeta (cut in small pieces) and heat to melt cheese, stirring constantly.
Cook the cavatelli noodles as directed on package. Thaw the broccoli. Add these last 2 ingredients to cheese sauce. Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: betty's cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss salad ingredients together.
Mix dressing well and pour over the salad before serving.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.
Crush one sleeve of Ritz crackers.
Mix with butter.
Cover top of casserole and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, soups and garlic salt; heat until bubbly.
Layer liquid, chicken and chips in a 3-quart casserole and top with cheese.
(The cheese can also be melted in with the soup mixture.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour and cornmeal.
Cream together sugar, salt, butter and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Add soda with last portion of the buttermilk.
Bake at 350° in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan until golden brown.

title: tijuana pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add canned goods and dash of chili powder.
Simmer until smoothly mixed.
In crock-pot, layer the Doritos, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese layer on top.
Heat until cheese melts.
A tasty Mexican-style casserole!

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix together.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil together.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight and serve. Keeps in refrigerator for a long time.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop dried beef in food processor until fine.
Reserve 1/2 cup of chopped beef.
Combine all ingredients except the 1/2 cup chopped beef into a large mixer bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle the reserved 1/2 cup of beef onto waxed paper.
Spoon cream cheese mixture onto the dried beef and form into ball.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Serve with crackers and enjoy.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend in blender for several minutes. Add 1 1/2 Tbsp. poppy seed and blend. Chill.

title: colonel harris' chicken stir-fry
directions: Rub curry powder on chicken and cook in 2 tablespoons of oil over medium heat.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add balance of oil and cook celery and onion over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes. Add flour and milk/water to make white sauce.
(You may also wish to add chicken broth).
Add cooked chicken and walnuts.
Mix well. Season with lemon pepper.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: banana walnut loaf
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; beat hard until light.
Add mashed banana.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda. Stir into creamed mixture.
Beat.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil and flavoring.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: chocolate salad
directions: Combine all in a large bowl and mix to distribute evenly. You may add other types of chocolate candy you wish.
SIT BACK AND ENJOY.

title: 1-2-3 barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small heavy saucepan.
Heat to simmering over medium heat.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Puree in batches in a blender until smooth.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and 2 cups sugar together until fluffy and light.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add flour mixture to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in fluffy beaten egg whites.
Spoon batter into 3 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add remaining sugar and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Add raisins, nuts, and coconut.
Stir in remaining vanilla and wine.
spread filling thickly between layers of cake and on top and sides.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil
noodles
per package directions.	Brown and drain sausage; crumble.
Add
to tomato sauce and spices.
Make 3 to 4 layers
of: lasagna noodles, a little sauce, Mozzarella and Cheddar
cheeses.
Cover
everything with rest of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes uncovered.

title: mashed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake until brown.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Combine the condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemonade.
Mix well and pour into crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: baked apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet; stir in sugars and cinnamon.
Add apples.
Cover and simmer until apples are soft.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Mix macaroni, onion, pimiento, grated cheese (reserve 1/2 cup cheese for topping), milk and mushroom soup together.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Continue to beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or cold.
Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chile rellenos
directions: Wash chiles, remove seeds and pat dry.
Combine grated Jack cheese with grated Cheddar cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer half chiles and half cheese.
Repeat layers, saving 1 cup cheese for top.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add Jell-O and gelatine mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen berries; mix and let congeal until thickens.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Crumble cake and stir into mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill. Cut into squares to serve.
This recipe is from Marguerite Sadler.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape and place in pan or baking dish.
Pour sauce over meat loaf and baste during baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream and add cherries.
Add cherry juice, blending well, until mixture reaches dip consistency.
Use as a dip for fresh, raw fruits.
Serves 15 people.

title: hello dolly 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs over the butter.
Sprinkle the coconut, then the chocolate bits, then the butterscotch bits.
Sprinkle the English walnuts next.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares; remove from pan.

title: english muffin pizzas(snack food)
directions: After you have browned the English muffins, spread sauce on each half, usually 1 to 2 tablespoons.
Lightly salt and pepper, then add veggies and a few drops of Tabasco sauce (optional) and oregano.
Cover with cheese, vary according to taste.
I like to use two different types.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or just before cheese starts to brown.
This is a quick, easy snack that everyone loves.
You can add meat if you desire, or use the vegetarian version given.
The thing that's great is that every pizza can be just a bit different with a different taste.
You can customize your pizza.

title: country style steak
directions: In a plastic bag, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Cut steak in bite size pieces.
Heat Crisco in large saucepan until hot.
Put steak in bag with flour; shake to coat.
Place meat in hot Crisco; brown on both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over steak and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in buttermilk (I use dry buttermilk mix and water) for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter mixture.
Coat with bread crumbs, salt and 1 tablespoon sesame seed mixture.
Place in 11 x 14-inch pan. Sprinkle each piece with sesame seed.
Pour excess butter over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Baste with any extra juices and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla pie
directions: Mix with mixer. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Chill and serve.

title: christmas cake cookies
directions: Discard date pits and cut dates in chunks; cut candied cherries in quarters.
Slice pineapple in thin slivers; blanch the almonds, chop them coarsely and toast until golden.
Chop Brazil nuts.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer in water until tender.
Cook spaghetti in broth. When done, mix other ingredients and put in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
