Add gelatin and cream cheese; heat until dissolved.
Add ice water. Set mixture in pan of ice water until it is partially set.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: tupperware bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except flour, mixing well. Add 5 cups plain flour, mixing well.
Add 5 more cups of flour to mixture, mixing well.
Put this is a Tupperware bowl and let rise in a warm place until double.
Pat down and divide in 3 sections. Put in 3 oiled loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate monkey
directions: In blender container, place chocolate milk and chocolate fudge sauce.
Add banana chunks.
Cover and blend until smooth. Through hole in lid of blender, add ice cubes, one at a time, while blender is running, until mixture is smooth.

title: merengues (little candy kisses)
directions: Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar while still beating, salt too.
When quite shiny, fold in vanilla and chocolate bits.
Drop by scant teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake one hour at 250°.
Do not double recipe.
It is better to do it twice. Makes 50 servings.

title: butter mints
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and butter in saucepan.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour on well buttered marble slab.
Drop 2 or 3 drops mint flavor on top.
When cool enough to handle, pull as long as you can.
Stretch on countertop.
Clip into desired sizes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken with forty cloves of garlic(french)
directions: Combine olive
oil, garlic and herbs in a deep roasting dish. Rinse chicken and
pat
dry.
Place chicken over garlic mixture. Drizzle with lemon	juice.	Sprinkle
with	salt and pepper. Place covered pot in
a 350° oven.	Bake until tender and juices run clear, about
hours.
Remove
cover and bake for 5 to 10	minutes
longer.
Carve
chicken
and
spoon cooking liquid over chicken.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
This is great for chips, crackers or veggies.

title: sweet-n-sour turkey meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
sauce.
Shape
into
small meatballs.	Brown in a
frying pan which has been sprayed with Pam or Mazola
spray.
Transfer
meatballs to crock-pot.
Pour on sweet and sour sauce.
Cook
on
high setting 1 to 2 hours. Serve from crock-pot.

title: peach squares
directions: Melt margarine and add to crumbs and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth. Fold in whipped cream.
Spread on graham cracker crumbs.
Top with sliced peaches.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
When Jell-O starts to thicken, pour over peaches.
Chill 3 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cook crust in the oven.
Put all the ingredients in a pan; mix them up and cook them on top of stove until thick.
Pour them into the already cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff; brown in oven.
This is the best pie; we really love it.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover, 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; let cool.
Peel and cut into 1/3-inch slices. Arrange slices in buttered casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cover sweet potatoes with sauce.
When ready to serve, place in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate munchin cake
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Stir with fork, scraping corners and sides of pan until mixture is uniform.

title: chewies
directions: Mix well the graham cracker crumbs, milk, chocolate chips and nuts. Spread into a buttered 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes (may take a little longer).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut and remove from pan while hot.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions in saucepan. Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Mix cream cheese and sour cream and add to meat mixture. Cook and drain noodles. Mix all ingredients in baking dish. Sprinkle with grated/shredded Cheddar cheese. Cover and put in oven. Cook until bubbly hot, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bean soup(serves 4)
directions: To avoid gas from beans soak beans in 9 cups water for a minimum of 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and discard water.
In a large pot over high heat, bring 9 cups water to a boil.
Add soaked beans and oil, to reduce foaming (may be omitted to reduce fat and top of liquid skimmed with a spoon), turn heat down to simmer.
Cover loosely and cook for 1 hour.
Drain water from beans and repeat previous step, cooking until beans are tender.
Drain again reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Dissolve seasonings from bag in this liquid and return to pot with beans.
Add liquid and tomatoes along with vegetables.
Serve hot with low-fat crackers for a well balanced meal.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, vanilla, almond extract and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients except granulated sugar/frosting. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half about 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly brown.
Let cool and frost or sprinkle with granulated sugar.

title: cornish pastry dough or pie and apple bar dough
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder and cut lard, until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
In 1 cup measuring cup break egg and add vinegar.
Fill with cold water.
Stir together.
Mix liquid with dry ingredients.
Roll thin, cut with 10-inch pot lid.
Fill and fold over, crimp, then roll edges.
Bake or spread 1/2 on cookie sheet.
Fill with apple pie filling top with second half. Bake for apple bars.
Bake 350° for about 1/2 hour or until brown on top.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together the apples, celery, walnuts and raisins.

title: strawberry-banana spread
directions: Mash strawberries and banana together.
Add cinnamon or nutmeg and serve immediately.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Cook onion, pepper and sausage.
Drain.
Melt cheese.
Mix together and spread on thin deli rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Freezes well baked or unbaked.
Also, can be heated in microwave if they have been cooked and frozen.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Fix Jell-O
according
to directions on box; add sugar, grated carrots, lemon juice and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until it	starts	to
set.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Pour in greased
mold
and chill until very firm.
Place finished product on decorated tray.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Place chopped pepper, onion and pineapple on paper towel to absorb liquid.
Mix all ingredients well together in large bowl. Reserve 3/4 cup pecans.
Shape cheese into ball.
Roll in reserved pecans.
Chill until 1/2 hour before serving.
Cheddar cheese is optional but makes ball more solid.
Use red and green peppers for holidays.

title: hot cranberry drink
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan; stir to dissolve sugar.
Heat over low flame 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 14 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise, eggs and onion with broccoli in bowl.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Sift soda and flour.
Drop by spoon on greased pan.
Smash with fork.
Bake at 325°.

title: chicken-vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to package directions and drain.
Meanwhile in a 2 quart sauce pan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion, celery and thyme until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add soups and milk; stir until smooth.

title: favorite meat marinade
directions: Mix ingredients with a whisk in a large bowl.
Pour over brisket, ribs or any other meat.
(If you cook in oven, leave meat in marinade while cooking.
It makes a wonderful sauce.)

title: onion soup gratinee
directions: Slice and mince onions.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add onions and peppercorns.
Cook, stirring constantly until light brown.
Sprinkle onions with flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add beef broth, water and bay leaf.
Bring to boil. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Discard bay leaf and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into ovenproof tureen.
Top with toast slices and sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese turns golden.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pie crust
directions: Take fork and add 1 tablespoon of water at a time to flour, shortening and salt until all is moistened.
Divide in half and roll out on floured sheet.
Press in pie plate.
Makes 2 pie crusts or top and bottom for 1 pie.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix well and bake about 1 hour in greased and floured loaf pan at 350°.

title: sauerkraut and smoked sausage
directions: Put kraut in baking dish.
Cut smoked sausage serving pieces. Place in kraut.
Bake in 350° oven until sausage pops when forked. Boil potatoes and mash.
Serve with kraut and sausage.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Put in pot.
Add soup, water and mushroom soup.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Very good and the gravy is good on mashed potatoes.

title: chicken skillet
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown well in butter in large skillet.
Add water, onion, salt and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add soup and vegetables to drippings in skillet.
Bring to boil on medium heat.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice, then top with chicken.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on the slices of white bread.
Next spread the grape jelly on top of peanut butter.
Put the sandwich together and eat.
Can be made the night before and taken to school for lunch.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Arrange crosswise in a baking dish.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and butter; microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir to mix.
Add vanilla and salt. Stir to blend. Pour onto buttered dish and put in refrigerator.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In large skillet, dissolve Jell-O, brown sugar, and salt in boiling water. Add butter and bring to boil. Add sweet potatoes, simmer, basting frequently until syrup thickens, about 15 minutes. Serves 6-8.

title: hamburger green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain off fat.
Stir in green beans and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Meantime, boil or steam potatoes until tender; drain and mash.
Add milk and margarine; add egg, mixing well.
Put meat mixture in casserole dish and layer potato mixture next, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: key largo roast pork
directions: Combine ingredients in plastic bag. Refrigerate overnight, turning bag occasionally. Roast pork until meat thermometer registers 170°. Allow about 30 minutes per pound. Midway through roasting, pour marinade over meat. Serves 6.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together and put in graham cracker crust. Chill and use your favorite fruit topping.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onions, and bell pepper. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 hour. Garnish with black olives, cheese, and sour cream. Serve with Doritos.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup.
Form balls and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup mushroom soup mixed with 1 can of water.
(I use 1/2 milk and 1/2 water.)
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften
cream cheese and butter, blend until smooth then add sugar
and
vanilla, beating again until smooth.
Spread on cake.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, peanut butter and butter and save 1/2 cup.
Add baking powder, baking soda, milk, eggs and vanilla. Blend until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, bottom greased only.
Sprinkle with crumbs and 6 ounces chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and pineapple.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish.
Melt butter in skillet and add bread cubes, lightly browning the cubes.
Pour bread cubes over pineapple mixture and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until firm.
Good with chicken or ham.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix together flour and milk until smooth. Melt butter and add to flour milk mixture. Spread this mixture over vegetables. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all the ingredients well, then add enough homogenized milk to fill a 1 gallon freezer.
Mix well and freeze to desired consistency.

title: aunt penny's oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger supper
directions: Fry onion and ground chuck until brown.
Add soup and water. Mix well and remove from stove.
Slice potatoes, then put into casserole dish.
Alternate with hamburger mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: new-wave macaroni and cheese
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine green onions, next 6 ingredients and 2 cups water.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 14 to 16 minutes, until macaroni is tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir in cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Blend milk into egg; add fat.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly and then mix in peanut butter only until mixture becomes crumbly.
Add liquid, stir slightly leaving batter lumpy.
Fill muffin tins half full with batter and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream shortening and cheese together; add sugar and continue creaming.
Beat egg yolk, vanilla, and orange rind together.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon together.
Mix all ingredients together. Place cookies on a cookie sheet and bake 12-15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: santa's cocoa
directions: Mix together.
Add 1/3 or 1/4 cup of mix to one mug of hot water.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: cheese cake pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 5 ingredients; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle evenly with pecans.
Combine the beaten eggs and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon over pecan layer.
Bake on the lowest rack for 35 minutes or until set. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, mushroom soup, onion, water chestnuts (optional), Cheez Whiz and half can of French fried onions.
Pour into casserole, adding the rest of French fried onions over top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy potato-carrot casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook potatoes and carrots, covered in boiling water, about 12 minutes or until carrots are tender; drain.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, salsa, milk and chilies to create sauce.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Layer chicken, torn tortillas, cheese and sauce in casserole dish (similar to lasagna). Refrigerate 24 hours before baking at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: breakfast coffee cake
directions: Combine yeast, warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar; set aside. Cream shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg until light and fluffy; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk to yeast mixture; add to creamed mixture alternately with the dry ingredients; mixing well after each addition.

title: congealed pink delight
directions: Make jello as directed on package. Add marshmallows and melt in hot jello. Add to softened cream cheese.

title: braunschweiger pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into a ball and roll in chopped parsley.

title: heather's carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add oil and beat until smooth. Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat until well mixed.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch layer cake pans or a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon. Set aside. Mix eggs, oil and vanilla. Add flour and nuts.
Add to apple mixture and mix. Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in large bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Slowly mix in the rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: roberta luce's cloverleaf rolls
directions: Scald milk, add sugar.
When lukewarm, add yeast mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1/2 of the flour, then egg, salt and melted shortening.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour enough to make as soft dough as can be handled.
Knead gently until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Roll 1/3-inch thick.
Cut into small circles.
Brush with melted butter.
Place three in each muffin cup.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: nancy's easy cake
directions: Mix together and bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: holiday special(link sausage with apples)
directions: Cover sausage with cold water.
Heat to boiling and drain. Place sausage in large baking dish.
Cover with pared sweet potatoes and onions.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and add apples.
Cover and bake slowly until fruit is tender.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit ball
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail well.
Put in processor. Mix with cream cheese and pudding.
Refrigerate for a while, then roll into a ball and roll in nuts, if desired.
Good with apple chips or cinnamon graham crackers.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: new orleans red beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or parboil 30 minutes.
Melt butter and saute onion, pepper and garlic until soft.
Remove pan from heat and blend in flour.
Add tomatoes gradually, stirring until smooth.
Return to heat and add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat until beans become soft, about 2 1/2 hours.
If liquid boils away, add a little water.
Mash a few of the soft beans to thicken if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave marshmallow treats
directions: Heat butter in 2-quart dish for 50 to 60 seconds, or until melted.
Stir in marshmallows, coating with butter.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Cook for another 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Mix until well coated.
Pat evenly into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: taglarania(easy one pan meal!)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet.
Salt to taste. Drain excess fat from browned ground beef.
While beef is browning cook egg noodles in boiling water until tender and drain.
Add noodles, tomato soup, cream of mushroom soup, creamed corn and/or peas into skillet and mix thoroughly and heat until bubbly.
Turn heat to simmer and place cheese slices over top of ground beef mixture and heat until cheese begins to melt.
Remove from heat and serve right from skillet.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat egg. Add pepper and salt. Add grated potato and onion. Use flour to thicken the mixture as desired.
Adding a grated apple also adds flavor.
Fry the cakes in hot fat, browning slowly on each side.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or other large pot, brown hamburger, peppers and onion in olive oil.
Add 6 to 8 cups water; bring to boil. Add remaining ingredients and allow to simmer until vegetables are tender, or longer.

This makes good soup for unexpected company. Add a little more water, another bouillon cube, an extra potato and anything else you have on hand (broccoli, cauliflower, can of beans, yesterday's leftovers, pasta, etc.).
Don't leave out garlic and oregano.
Add thyme or basil if you wish.

title: dark sweet cherry salad
directions: Dissolve all 3 packages of Jell-O in boiling water, not cold. Stir until dissolved.
Then put in drained cherries.
Don't use liquid.
Put in pineapple with juice.
Slice bananas and put them in. Pour into mold until half full.
Put in the refrigerator for about an hour until congealed.
Then put on a layer of sour cream, then put rest of Jell-O mixture in mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot mushroom snacks
directions: Mince mushrooms and mix with softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and blend.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Pour in spinach liquid and cream slowly.
Cook until smooth and creamy.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until melted. Combine with spinach in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice 5 minutes; add slowly and stir in dry ingredients.
Pour on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Turn out on towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream sugar, salt, melted butter and egg.
Alternate milk and flour last and blueberries.
Bake in muffin tins in 400° oven.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Pour blueberries into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with white sugar and lemon juice.
Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Blend in flour and oats with fork.
Spread mixture over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fried catfish
directions: Cut the fish into steaks or slice for frying.
Salt and bread the fish in
the meal.
In a frypan with the cooking oil hot, place the fish
and
fry 8 to 10 minutes, turning to make sure of an
even
brown.
Depending
on
the
thickness of the fish, more or less cooking time may be needed.

title: cherry patch cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and then add to that mixture, the last 3 ingredients.
Take 2/3 of mixture and press on cookie sheet, slightly greased.
Spread 2 cans of cherry pie filling on top.
Cut other 1/3 of mixture (roll out first) into strips.
Lay strips onto pie filling.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: roast turkey
directions: Follow directions on turkey for preparing the turkey for roasting.
Stuff the turkey with apples, celery and carrots.
Bake turkey in a cooking bag according to directions on turkey.
The apples and vegetables will make the turkey very moist and give a bit of a sweet flavor to the meat.
(You may increase or decrease number of apples and vegetables according to the size of your turkey.)

title: honey (?)-mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Adjust to your taste.
Use especially for potato salad.
It is also nice for cole slaw or any food in which you want a sweeter dressing.
(All ingredients are adjustable to taste.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a square baking dish.
Follow directions and mix your Stove Top stuffing; set aside.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 can of water; set aside.
Tear or cut up chicken and place on bottom of baking dish.
Put a layer of stuffing next.
Put soup on top.
When all ingredients are used, put in oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put in casserole with Pepperidge Farm herbal mix on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla. Mix well. Beat in zucchini. Sift dry ingredients and blend well together.
Fold in nuts. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain well, beat eggs, blend in mayonnaise, onion, pepper and thyme.
Stir in well-drained squash. Spoon mixture into a greased shallow casserole.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese and paprika.
Bake 25 minutes in a 375° oven or until puffed and lightly browned.

title: walnut vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli; slice in half lengthwise.
In small bowl, combine broth, cornstarch, tamari, sherry and sugar; set aside.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients.
(You may add more or less olives, depending on your liking.)
Before serving, stuff celery rib with cream cheese mixture or you can dip the celery.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Slice each package of rolls horizontally like a sandwich; set aside.
Melt the margarine and then add mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Brush this mixture on both sides of the sliced rolls.
Layer ham and Swiss cheese on the bottom portion of the rolls and then put the top on.
Heat about 10 minutes at 400°.

title: zipilli dough
directions: Mix the first three ingredients in bowl.
Dissolve yeast cakes in 2 cups of warm water.
Beat in eggs.
Add to flour ingredients and 2 cups water.
Keep mixing by hand until all is mixed.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Take tablespoon at a time and drop into hot fat.
Makes 80.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend Key lime juice and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip and fold in until smooth.
Add food coloring as desired for your preference.
Pour into honey graham cracker prepared crust or Oreo cookie crust.
Refrigerate until firm (overnight is best).
You can top a slice of pie with a dollop of Cool Whip and slice of fresh lime.

title: pizza
directions: Get some dough.
Get a round pan.
Cook the dough.
Put tomato sauce on.
Put toppings on.
Put cheese on.
Cook for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: turkey legs
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except turkey legs, mixing well.
Place turkey legs in shallow pan.
Pour sauce over and cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove foil and baste legs with sauce.
Return to oven, uncovered, for about 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.
Very good!

title: whiskey sauce
directions: Cook ingredients until butter melts; remove from heat.
Add whiskey.
Serve on bread pudding.

title: golfer's soup
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring water, bouillon cubes, onions and celery to boil and cook for twenty minutes covered.
Add carrots, potatoes and vegetables, cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup, Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese melts and serve.

title: ruth's scalloped hash browns
directions: Allow frozen hash browns to thaw slightly until mixable.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in deep-dish casserole and bake at 350° until hot about 1 hour.
Yummy with ham!

title: african rice
directions: Fry onion, green pepper, mixed vegetables and broccoli in oil until tender.
Add Rice-A-Roni and 1/4 cup water.
Fry together. Add smoked turkey and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook chicken
and
reserve cooking water.
Remove bones and skin and
cut
up.
Cook
rice according to package directions using
reserved water.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: mud
directions: Melt peanut butter, butter & chocolate chips. Add vanilla and pour over Chex cereals. Mix well. Let cool. Put powdered sugar in large brown paper bag, add chex cereals. Shake well. Add nuts and M&M's, toss lightly. Tore in air tight container. Great snack!

title: raisin-apple spice cake
directions: In a saucepan combine raisins and diced apples.
Add water to cover.
Cook until tender, making sure you have 1 cup liquid after removing fruit.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch bottom of pan; line with graham crackers. Mix Cool Whip and instant pudding (already mixed with milk); spread 1/2 on top of crust, then another layer of crust.
Spread the other 1/2 of Cool Whip on the crackers, then another layer of crackers.
Add topping.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Mix cheese, milk, beef, onion and peppers.
Put in Pyrex pie or quiche dish (8-inch).
Sprinkle with nuts.
Can be made ahead and cooked later or frozen and reheated.
Cook until bubbly. Double recipe for 10-inch pie pan.
Serves 8.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Place piece of suet or butter in a heavy roasting pan (with a domed lid, preferably a Dutch oven).
Brown until bottom of pan is glazed.
Remove suit and brown beef on all sides.
Remove from pan and remove any grease on bottom of pan.
Put beef back in, fat side down.
Add sprinkle of vinegar and onions.
Cook approximately 4 to 5 hours.
Turn midway.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water, strawberries and banana in blender, then pour in ice trays and freeze. When frozen and you get ready for them, pour them in a punch bowl. Pour pineapple juice and ginger ale over the frozen cubes, then serve.

title: sunday roast
directions: Season roast
with
salt,
pepper
and	garlic	salt to taste. Line
a
baking
pan
with foil, allowing enough extra foil to form
a
pouch around the roast.
Place roast in foil-lined pan. Mix soup and soup mix.
Spread mixture over roast. Seal foil around
roast
tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
The soup mixture makes a delicious gravy to serve over rice.

title: taco sauce
directions: Cook in pan 2 hours.
Put in sterilized jars.
Seal; put in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: mushroom appetizers
directions: Rinse mushrooms in cool water and let dry.
Remove stems. Paint buttons with corn oil and roll them in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with cheese.
Place in preheated oven at 250° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
May prepare stems the same way.

title: creamy pecans
directions: Cook sugars and sour cream over low heat, stirring constantly until it forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until coating forms on nuts and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: 50 year old pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt tube pan.
Cream sugar, Crisco and one egg at a time until creamy.
Add buttermilk, flour and soda alternately; beat until blended.
Add flavorings last.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until done.

title: chicken creole style
directions: Prepare chicken for frying with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: fajitas and marinade
directions: Put coarse ground pepper and garlic powder on both sides of meat and place in long Pyrex dish.
Squeeze 2 lemons over meat. Add soy sauce, wine or vinegar and chopped garlic.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let stand for 2 to 4 hours.
Cook on high heat on grill, using marinade to baste while cooking.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine in a glass pie dish. Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Spoon 1 can pie filling over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Lower heat to 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
You can use any pie filling.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco together well.
Add 3 tablespoons
flour	and
1	egg alternately until all is used; beat
well.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Pour into well-greased and
floured
tube
cake pan.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Start
in
cold
oven!
After 1 hour, turn oven to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill-cucumber sauce
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add all ingredients, except cucumber, to processor bowl.
Process until mixture is smooth.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Stir in chopped cucumber.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: almond bar
directions: Melt candy in top of double boiler (just keep warm water; don't boil).
Spread shelled almonds on cookie sheet and toast in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place almonds in jelly roll pan lined with wax paper.
Pour chocolate over and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together egg, butter, sugars and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix until all blended well.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls
2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Allow to cool before removing from sheet.
Makes about 24 to 30 cookies.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan with tortillas.
Layer half of the meat mixture over the tortillas and then sprinkle with 1 c. of cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: d.o. meatballs
directions: Combine beef, rice, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and onion. Shape into
meatballs and put into 12-inch Dutch oven. Mix soup and
water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Crush potato chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brother danny's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda.
In a bowl, beat the butter with mixer on medium for 30 seconds.
Add both sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat until well combined.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pepperoni 'n cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place 3 slices of pepperoni, slightly overlapped, on center of each triangle; top each with quartered cheese slice.
Roll up; place rolls point side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Curve into crescent shape.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: iron skillet plain cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar and shortening together.
Add milk and flavoring.
Beat well.
Add eggs, beat 2 more minutes.
Can bake in iron skillet or two 8-inch cake pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter oaties
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Allow to set for several hours.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: max's chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Wish-Bone Italian dressing one hour.
Roll and cover in "Kellogg's Corn Flakes" crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover.

title: ever crisp sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in stone jar and cover with water-lime solution.
Let soak 24 hours, stirring often with a wooden spoon. Rinse well 3 times with cold water.
Cover with cold water and let soak 3 hours.
Drain and cover with vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Let soak overnight.
In the morning, boil entire mixture 35 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.

title: tasty oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add flour and oatmeal and mix together.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Shape in rolls.
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: yellow deluxe cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately. Beat well after each addition.
Pour batter in 3 greased layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix in large container.
Save ginger ale until in bowl.
It takes about 1/2 bottle per bowl to taste right.
Crushed fruit (use blender) can be added also if desired.
Can make ice rings of appropriate fruits and color.
Must be done prior to be well frozen.
Flavor and color to suit colors of wedding.

title: delicious dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with vegetable sticks, broccoli, carrots, cauliflower and mushrooms.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil peppers, sugar and vinegar for 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then strain.
Add Sure-Jell and few drops green cake coloring.
Can.

title: deannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Put butter, sugar, chocolate and milk in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan on stove.
Boil one minute on medium heat.
Takes about 5 minutes to come to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes about 4 dozen large cookies.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, add the cream cheese, cottage cheese and 1 1/2 cups white sugar; beat well with an electric beater.
Add the eggs, lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Add the cornstarch, flour and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add the sour cream; beat well.
Pour into a 10-inch spring pan (it should be a good quality aluminum pan), generously greased with butter.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer. When pecan pie is done, outer edge of filling should be set and center slightly soft.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll in mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Place coated biscuit pieces into greased Bundt pan.
Bring to a boil 1 cube of butter and remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over top of biscuit pieces in pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: winter cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a large stock pot or Dutch oven, saute onion and celery in oil until soft.
Add ground chuck and brown.
Add remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candy bar fudge
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with foil. Butter the foil and set pan aside. Cut candy bars into 1/2-inch slices; set aside. In a heavy saucepan, bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil over medium heat. Cook and stir until a candy thermometer reads 234° (soft-ball stage), about 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla until smooth. Pour half into prepared pan. Sprinkle with candy bar slices. Top with remaining chocolate mixture and spread evenly. Let stand at room temperature.

title: weight watcher key lime pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-o in hot water. Let cool for 10 minutes. Mix cooled Jell-o and remaining ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. You can garnish with slices of fresh lime or graham cracker crumbs. Refrigerate for several hours before cutting.

title: male cooking outdoors
directions: Have your wife season meat and remind her to buy a 20-pound bag of briquets and lug home.
Ask where matches are.
Ask where briquets are.
Ask where charcoal starter is.
Start fire with great gusts of soot and smoke.
Ask for water to put out fire in meat.
Ask what time it is.
Ask how long meat has been cooking. Is it done when similar in appearance to charcoal?

title: dutch honey bread
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together.
Add the buttermilk, egg and honey; blend well.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: percolator punch
directions: In bottom of coffeepot, pour cranberry juice, pineapple juice and water.
In coffee basket, put cinnamon, sugar, salt and cloves.
Perk for regular time.
(For 30 cups, do 4 times this recipe.)

title: low cal cabbage salad
directions: Put cabbage, peppers and onion in a bowl and set aside.
In a pot bring to boil vinegar, Sweet and Low|, celery seed, mustard seed, and salt.
Cool slightly. Pour over cabbage mixture. Let stand in refrigerator at least 4 hours.

title: string bean salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press into bottom of large cookie sheet with sides.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes; cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread onto the baked crust; top with the chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Serve cut into squares.
Can be used for luncheons, appetizers or refreshments at club.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend dry ingredients; stir in.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix together, adding flour gradually, adding ground almonds fast.
Now make loaves approximately 4 x 10-inch.
Wrap loaves in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
When ready to bake, slice loaves and bake (they do swell so try a couple first), resembling a bar cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 dozen.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls 2
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling, salted water for 5 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain leaves.
Combine ground beef, eggs, onion, rice, butter salt, and pepper;
mix well.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each leaf; fold ends over and roll up.
Place cabbage rolls, seam side down, in a large greased skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over cabbage rolls.

title: simple fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in shallow baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together well and pour into margarine.
Do not stir.
Add fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over crust and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: fiesta bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together oil and lime juice; add cilantro, cumin and salt and pepper to taste, mixing well.
Stir in beans, bell pepper, corn, onion and jalapeno pepper.
Taste and adjust seasoning.

title: guilt-free cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth (mixture will be dry).
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, with a wire whisk until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese, salt and pepper; stir until cheese melts.
Serve sauce over broccoli or other vegetables.
Yield: 1 cup (about 20 calories per tablespoon).

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° until done in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: ashley's crab puffs
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine mayonnaise, shrimp, scallions, pepper, lemon and salt to taste.
Beat the egg whites until stiff. Gently fold in shrimp or crab mixture.
Spoon a mound on each bread round.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Put under broiler until lightly brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 48 puffs.

title: tofu and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes; drain well on layers of paper towels.
Separate and rinse cabbage; pat dry.
Cut leaves crosswise into 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 3 tablespoons soy sauce; set aside.

title: meatballs with sotanghon
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients together.
Form into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Saute garlic in lard, add onion and broth.
Boil.
While boiling, drop meatballs, one by one.
Cook until meat is almost done.
Add the sotanghon and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Season with toyo and pepper.
Pour into a soup tureen or bowl.
Sprinkle with green onion and serve hot.

title: crumb coated chicken(microwave recipe)
directions: Beat eggs with butter and salt in a small bowl.
Place crumbs in a shallow plate.
Coat chicken in crumbs, then egg mixture, then again in crumbs.
Arrange chicken pieces in 8-inch square dish. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 18 to 22 minutes, rotating chicken 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.

title: swiss cheese potatoes
directions: Thaw frozen potatoes slightly.
Combine with whipping cream, cheese, butter, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: pork and rice
directions: Brown chops on both sides. Remove chops.
Cook onion, celery and green pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt, sugar, Tabasco sauce and bay leaf. Cover and cook.
Serve over 1 1/2 cups long grain cooked rice.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine mix, oranges, oil and eggs and beat 2 or 3 minutes until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans. Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven or until done.
Cool in pans and remove to cake racks.
Combine remaining items and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Let rest 5 minutes and spread between layers and on top and sides.
Chill at least 2 hours. Garnish with orange curls.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Drain the corn and place into casserole dish.
Add beaten eggs, cream, grated cheese and salt and pepper.
Stir and place into a preheated oven at 325° and bake approximately 50 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix the oil, dressing, dill weed and garlic powder well.
Pour over crackers and stir often.
Ready in 1 hour.
No baking.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put oleo, cocoa and water into a saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, cinnamon, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix and put into a greased baking sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peach raisin deep dish cobbler
directions: Roll out 2/3 of dough on lightly floured surface to fit 10 x 6-inch baking dish or any size you prefer.

title: cornflake squares
directions: Mix together brown sugar, peanut butter and corn syrup.
Put in microwave; boil until bubbles, stirring once or twice.
Add 2 cups peanuts and the cornflakes.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: english apple pie
directions: Place ingredients in pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in a casserole.
Top with mixture of the Bisquick, milk and melted margarine or butter. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: tortellini calcutta
directions: Heat olive oil and butter; add onion and garlic.
Cook until soft.
Add carrots; cook 4 minutes.
Add basil; cook 2 minutes. Add tomatoes; put sauce back into pan.
Add cream and curry.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve over pasta with freshly grated cheese.
Enjoy!

title: frozen cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and soak in salt for 2 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Combine sugar, vinegar and sliced onions and pour over cucumbers.
Put in freezer packages of any size you like.
Freeze and then thaw as you use the packages.
Just thaw and put on table.

title: chewies
directions: Melt butter in pot with brown sugar.
Stir well.
Add flour and eggs.
Stir well.
Add nuts and stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: johnny cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Mix together flours and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan (not floured). Can be frozen.
Serve with butter and hot syrup.
Also serve sausage, etc., for a great brunch!

title: ground beef grand
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Mix together with beef.
Bake in 2-qt. casserole at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Place biscuits on top; finish baking at 375 degrees for about 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: sea-land chowder
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Skin fillets and cut in pieces about 1 inch square.
In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add the potatoes, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the fish and simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, and potatoes are tender.
Add the milk and corn.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve hot; garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: date bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes a stiff batter.
I usually have to put butter on my hands and press this in a greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good Christmas cookie bar.
Sprinkle the top with a little powdered sugar.

title: great grandma's divinity
directions: Heat sugar, water, syrup and salt. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cook without stirring until mixture reaches hard-ball stage.

title: cheryl's spaghetti
directions: Cook hamburger in deep pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Cut up and add whole tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add oregano, minced onion, mushrooms, sugar and garlic salt.
Stir occasionally on low heat.
Be careful that it doesn't burn on bottom.
Add water if it is too thick.
The ingredients that don't have measurements can be added to your desire.
Put over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Add cereal and stir until cereal is well coated.
Put powdered sugar in a brown paper grocery sack.
Add cereal mixture and shake until cereal is coated.

title: cream cheese fruit dip
directions: Cream together the marshmallow and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Best when served with sliced apples.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Put pineapple in small pan and stir in jello.
Heat until it comes to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, mix in Cool Whip and cottage cheese until smooth.
Serves 12 or 16.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix in pan you are going to bake it in.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in sugar and water mixture.
Add warm milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour to make soft dough. Let stand 10 minutes.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Grease top and cover.
Let rise double in bulk.
Cut into rolls.
Let rise until when finger is punched in dough it leaves an imprint. Bake rolls at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cake
directions: Mix together and bake in slow oven at 325°.

title: e z old fashion brownies
directions: Mix sugar and chocolate.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cream together.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: noodle-corn casserole
directions: Precook noodles; drain.
Lightly brown onion rings in butter. Add half of cooked noodles to 3-quart casserole bowl or 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add 1 pint of sour cream on top of noodles. Add half of onion rings.
Add 1 can creamed corn.
Repeat these layers again.
Put several pads of butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° until hot (about 30 minutes).

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars and add remaining ingredients as listed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until lightly browned; do not overbake.

title: danish chicken
directions: Coat thighs in seasoned flour.
Fry in margarine until very brown.
Put in small roaster pan with drippings.
Add mushrooms and juice.
Sprinkle thyme over it, along with onion (sliced), bay leaf and bacon.
Add lots of white wine and cook slowly until tender at about 250°.
Cook covered and keep adding wine if cocktail hour drags on.
Serve over rice.
Makes lots of good juice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time. Add salt and flavoring.
Add soda to buttermilk and then rotate flour and the buttermilk mixture to the Crisco and sugar mixture. Spray Bundt pan with Pam and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Separate eggs, placing whites in a large bowl.
Beat whites until soft peaks form.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add milk and flavoring.
Beat well. Whip cream and fold gently into eggnog.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Serves 16.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Brown onion in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except for hot dogs, and cook together several minutes.
Split hot dogs and put into sauce.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain. Saute meat, onions, celery and bell pepper. Add soup, mushrooms and cream cheese. Add broccoli to meat mixture. Mix well. Salt and pepper to taste. Bake pie crusts. Add half of mixture to each crust. Top with Mozzarella cheese and bread crumbs. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's southern potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until fork-tender.
Refrigerate until cool. Peel.
Chop potatoes and 5 eggs.
Reserve 1 egg for garnish.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Blend together sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and cook until thickens.
Just before removing from stove, stir in egg yolks (save whites for meringue).
Add butter.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Thaw dough according to package directions. Flatten dough and put pizza sauce or Ragu over it (desired amount). Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over the sauce. Add Provolone slices (about 3 to a loaf). Add pepperoni slices (spaced out), then put sausage over this. Roll up like a jelly roll and place in loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Put flour in dry 1 1/2 quart Dutchoven.
Cook over low heat until light brown, stirring frequently. Add onion and diced tomatoes; cook until onions are translucent.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except shrimp, mixing well.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until green pepper is tender and sauce is bubbly; stir often.
Add shrimp.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are hot; stir once or twice.
Do not overcook or shrimp will become tough.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yogurt banana sips
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Makes 2 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: quick and easy beef barley soup
directions: Place beef pieces and cooking liquid, water, bouillon granules and thyme in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add barley, green beans and carrots, stirring to combine.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 12 minutes, or until barley is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Stir in water and egg. Add milk. Cook until thick. Beat in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust. Cool.

title: special baked chicken
directions: Run cold water over dried beef.
Drain and arrange in the bottom of a 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place halved chicken breasts over beef.
Top each half with a slice of bacon.
Sprinkle a bit of rosemary on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Continue baking 40 to 50 minutes longer, depending on size of the breasts. This can also be baked longer in a slower oven if late guests delay dinner.
Serves 6.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans on large round platter.
Spread picante sauce over beans; layer sour cream over picante sauce, then lettuce, black olives, tomatoes, green onions and grated cheese on top.
Arrange tortilla chips around edge of dip on platter.
If you want to make this more of a meal, you can fix ground round like you would for tacos and layer it on top of beans; then other layers over meat.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in zipper type plastic bag. Shake with chicken, pork chops, etc.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Cover with foil for the first 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add rice in bottom of baking dish; add cream of chicken soup, then the broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, then add sauteed celery and onion.
Cover with Cheez Whiz; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream
cheese
and
butter.
Add
sugar and flavor.
Add eggs. Add
flour, a little at a time.
Be sure it is mixed and smooth. Pour
into
a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: coffee-chocolate chip bars
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together sugar and butter; beat in egg, coffee and vanilla.
Stir together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in butter mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 250°.
Melt caramels, margarine and milk in a pan.
Pour over cake.
Add chocolate chips and nuts. Add rest of batter on top of this.
Turn oven up to 350° and bake for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add milk.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Sprinkle a bit of sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt and cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles and put in casserole dish.
Stir in ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Cut up pepperoni in small pieces.
Stir in.
Bake until bubbly at 350° or heat in microwave until bubbly.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour
into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel apples
directions: Stick wooden skewers into stem end of apples.
Combine corn syrup, cream and butter.
Cook over low heat; add vanilla.
Dip apples into syrup (work fast).
Roll in coarsely chopped nuts, if desired.
Place upright on well-greased cookie sheet to cool.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk and roll in seasoned flour. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch deep pan.
Put chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Turn and bake for 15 minutes more.
Mix remaining buttermilk with soup and pour around chicken.
Bake for 15 minutes longer or until tender.
This is delicious!

title: frog eyed salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Add lemon juice. Cool mixture to room temperature. Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons salt and oil to boil. Add Spezziello. Cook at rolling boil until macaroni is done. Drain macaroni, rinse, drain again and cool to room temperature. Combine egg mixture and Spezziello. Mix lightly but thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight in air tight container. Add remaining 6 ingredients. Mix lightly but thoroughly. Refrigerate in airtight container until chilled. Salad may be refrigerated for as long as a week in airtight container. Can be frozen, but freezing changes texture somewhat. Makes 25 + servings.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Chop bacon and onion.
Cook in skillet over medium heat until onion is brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Butter an angel food cake pan. Coat the pan with graham cracker crumbs.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix with a spoon until blended.
Shape into balls, walnut size.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned crock mincemeat
directions: Cook meat and allow to cool.
Grind with uncooked suet.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Add enough brandy to moisten.
Let stand for 3 weeks, then add sherry (keep moist).
This will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.
When ready to bake pies, use 1 cup finely chopped apples and 1 1/2 cups mincemeat.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Top with lattice top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: coconut fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat or in a microwave. Stir until smooth and cool to room temperature.
Beat eggs at high speed until creamy.
Add sugar and beat 1 minute.
At low speed, blend in flour and cooled chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool (pie will settle) and serve with whipped cream.

title: cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight. (Do not use aluminum ware). Wash 3 or 4 times in clear water and soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours. Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a low boil to make syrup. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add cucumbers and soak 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Boil pickles in soaking liquid for 35 minutes. Fill jars with cucumber slices and pour syrup over cucumbers leaving 1/8-inch headspace. Put lids on each filled jar. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath method. Label and store in dry, dark, cool place.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecan meal. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Stir in Cool Whip; chill. Spread on cooled crust. Mix pudding and milk according to package directions. Pour immediately on second layer. Top with additional Cool Whip and chopped pecans. Refrigerate until serving. Cut into squares.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook to the soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add 2/3 cup peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until firm, then put in an 11 x 7-inch glass pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, water and syrup to boil.
Add peanuts and coloring.
Cook until hard boil stage; it makes a fine hair. Remove from heat; add butter and salt.
Beat by hand until mixture is thick to beat.
Pour on greased cookie sheet; cool.

title: banana nut bread(low calorie)
directions: Mix all together, beating egg whites and folding in later. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves two.
Equals 1 fruit serving, 1 choice group, 8 ounces skim milk and 1 egg.

title: hot rolls
directions: Measure in mixing bowl the sugar and 2 cups lukewarm water. Add yeast mixture (1/2 cup lukewarm water, yeast, salt and Crisco).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 3 cups flour and mix well. Add 3 more cups flour; mix well.
Let stand until double in size. Make into rolls and let rise again.
Bake in 425° oven.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs in a bowl.
Add milk, bread and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: easy denver sandwiches
directions: Spread margarine over 4 slices of bread.
Cook and stir onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon of margarine and the shortening in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl with a lid.
Shake. To serve, add three teaspoons mix to 1 cup hot water.
This mixture can be stored and used up to 8 months.
Just shake before using.
(Great for Christmas to put in a canning jar and give as a hostess gift!)

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and 1/2 cup water in a 4-cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 3 minutes; stir thoroughly.
Cook on High (maximum power) for 6 to 8 minutes, or until small amount of mixture dropped in cold water forms a hard ball (250° on candy thermometer).
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites in large bowl with electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
When syrup is ready, pour in a very thin, slow stream into egg whites.
Beat constantly with mixer on high.
Add vanilla; beat 6 to 8 minutes, or until mixture is stiff and loses its shine.
Fold in nuts; drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When cool, store in airtight container.
Can be tinted with food coloring.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: In wok or large skillet heat corn oil over medium-high heat. Add broccoli and cauliflower and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add red pepper; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove.
Add strips of steak and stir-fry 3 minutes or until beef is browned. Return vegetables. Stir in 1 cup of stir-fry sauce mix.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil for 1 minute.
Serves 4.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put butter, water and cocoa into saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir slightly and pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Do not overcook.

title: no-dough fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and baking powder; add milk and stir until blended.
Spoon batter over butter in baking dish; do not stir. Combine fruit and 1/2 cup sugar; spoon over batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 350°
for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: make your own sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Process in blender until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 14 ounces.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Power Level:
Medium-high (70%).
Total Cooking Time: 20 to 25 minutes.
Recipe Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: mother langdale's no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Toss well.
Mix the remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar melts and bring to a full boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Drop on waxed paper while warm.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Let cool in a blender.
Mix juices and bananas.
Blend well.
Stir in sugar-water.
Freeze and serve with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: peanut butter blossom
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix together.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put Hershey's Kisses in center as soon as baking finished.
Put in fridge to harden up a little.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples and water in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients together and mix until this resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle this over the apples and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serves 6.
Delicious with ice cream.

title: oven smoked beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket roast generously with celery salt and garlic salt.
Rub well with liquid smoke.
Seal in foil and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, without opening, bake at 350° for 1 hour. reduce heat to 275° and cook for three more hours.
Chill sauce; remove fat.
Reheat sauce and serve with brisket.
Cut brisket on bias.
Brisket is always moist and tender and is great for sandwiches.

title: italiano main dish soup
directions: Shape beef into bite size meatballs; brown.
Cook onion with garlic and oregano in a small amount of shortening or beef drippings until tender.
In a large kettle, gradually stir water into bean with bacon soup.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Heat to slow boil and cook until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cheese.

title: peanut candy
directions: Mix all this together.
Turn heat on high for a few moments and then turn on medium heat.
Cook 10 or 15 minutes.
Pinch soda.

title: nacho dip texas-style
directions: Brown the meat and sausage in a Dutch oven or saucepot; drain. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook until the Velveeta cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 8 cups.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Beat ingredients well with mixer until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Decorate cake with cherry pie filling.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine above ingredients together, spread in a pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: zip lock bag ice cream
directions: Combine milk, sugar, vanilla and peanut butter (if desired) in quart size bag.
Zip closed.
Place ice and rock salt in gallon bag.
Place quart bag in gallon bag.
Seal the bag.
Shake, roll, or mush the bag for about 5 minutes or until you get ice cream. Open the gallon bag and remove the quart size bag.
Dip quickly in water and dry the outside of the bag (to remove the salt from the bag).
Enjoy the ice cream!

title: hidden surprise salad
directions: Wash the lettuce under cold running water.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and measure 2 cups, packing lightly into measuring cup.
Put 1 cup of the lettuce into 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Put sieve over small bowl.
Empty the can of fruit cocktail into the sieve to drain (save juice to use another time).

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Pour in water and bring to a boil.
Add rice; cover and remove from stove.
Let set 5 minutes.
Pour in corn and soup; add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: porto rican beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil
beans and ham hocks or ham pieces until almost done.
Fry
ground beef, onion and garlic. Add one can of tomatoes and green chilies and season to taste.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Beat
eggs and box of brown sugar together until foamy. Add 1 tablespoon cold water.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Beat mixture
again.
Add
flour,
pecans
and orange slices. Stir the 2 mixtures until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake
25 minutes in moderate oven.
While still warm, cut in squares.
Lift out with spatula and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add steak, onion and garlic.
Cook until meat is brown.
Add green peppers and bouillon; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, water and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture and cook until thickened and clear.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Cut up tomatoes and mix with beans.
Mix cornbread and pour on top of ingredients.
Pour ingredients in an oblong pan and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Simmer sliced onions in a little water until tender.
Add butter while onions are hot.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese on top, then the pepper.
Heat the soup, milk and soy sauce; blend well.
Pour over onions and cheese.
Top with French bread slices that have been buttered; the slices should not be very thick and cut in fourths.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and slightly browned.

title: party potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle potato chips or corn flakes on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: blueberry-banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add bananas and other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: russian rock cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
(Use 1 cup of flour to dredge raisins and nuts.)
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and nuts, then soda in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Blend in carrots, raisins and nuts, mixing well after each.
Bake in round pan or 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Drain.
Set aside.
Melt oleo in large heavy saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Slowly add milk; cook over medium heat until bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Add macaroni. Pour into 8 x 7-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin pie with graham cracker crust(low-fat recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni with marinated tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except macaroni shells.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours but no longer than 24 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon.
Saute onion.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Pour this over the top when finished.
Stir margarine and peanut butter over low heat until melted.
Add powdered sugar; stir until it is blended.
Press into greased 11 x 13-inch pan and add melted chocolate as directed.

title: apricot spice bars
directions: Chop apricots fine.
Cream together butter, brown sugar and honey.
Beat eggs into creamed sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves and add to creamed sugar.
Mix walnuts with apricots and mix into flour and sugar.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 15 minutes, then glaze with 3/4 cup sifted confectioners sugar mixed with and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: tea cooler punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Allow to set 2 to 3 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add juices and sugar.
Stir well to dissolve. Cool.
Just before serving, place in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and ice ring.

title: chicken almondine
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients.
Cook until hot and bubbly.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch ungreased baking dish.
Top with unbaked crescent rolls.
Combine butter, cheese and almonds. Spread over crescent rolls.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until crescent rolls are brown.

title: quick cherry or apple crisp
directions: Pour the pie filling in an 8-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with the 1 cup white or yellow cake mix.
Pour melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sweet potato casserole(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Peel and whip with butter, milk and sugar to taste as you would for a sweet potato pie.
Layer as follows: layer of sweet potatoes, layer of sprinkled brown sugar, layer of pecan pieces, layer of sliced banana.
Make several layers.
Bake until hot.
Just before serving, top with marshmallows and brown in oven.

title: old-time rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, shortening, salt, egg and 1 cup flour.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining 2 cups flour and beat until dough crawls up beaters. Cover with wet towel and let rise in warm place for 1 hour, or until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Pour onto floured board and knead until easy to handle.
Shape as desired.
Place in pan and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Suitable for freezing.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In bowl, put salmon and juice.
Add eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Crush crackers and add enough to hold mixture together, about 1 tube or a little more.
Form into patties and fry in oil.

title: honolulu cooler - luau
directions: Make simple syrup by boiling sugar and water 5 minutes; set aside.
Combine tea and fruit juices.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and syrup to taste.
Garnish with orange slices and mint sprigs.
Makes 12 servings.

title: teriyaki chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat wok or 12 inch skillet over high heat.
Add oil; rotate wok to coat sides.	Add chicken; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Stir in remaining ingredients except couscous.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer about 6 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve with couscous, rice or noodles.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together in a jar.
Use 2 1/2 teaspoons per cup.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill pie plate or dish 2/3 full with sliced, peeled apples.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top of apples.
In bowl, mix melted margarine, 1 cup sugar, flour, egg and chopped walnuts.
Mixture will be very thick. Spread mixture over apples.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
It's quick, easy and delicious.
Serve warm, top with vanilla ice cream.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except soup.
Shape in small balls, cover with tomato soup (diluted) and a few grains of salt. Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Take chicken and use meat hammer to tenderize lightly.
Melt butter and add garlic salt to completely cover top of butter.
Dip chicken in butter and garlic salt.
Place in baking pan that has been covered with Pam spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then take off foil and bake 10 more minutes to brown.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Boil soup.
Gradually add gelatin and cream cheese.
Blend well.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into mold.
(Use with Escort crackers.)

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, brown onions and green peppers until tender in bacon grease.
Mix all together.
Bake in 2-quart covered casserole for 45 minutes at 375°.
Great with baked ham or a barbecue.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Cover top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice terrific
directions: Combine all in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and serve alone or with a veggie.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat sour cream into ingredients.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes in crust.

title: honey spice snaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Beat in honey and egg.
Beat extra well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Chill.
This is important.
Shape dough into small balls.
Dip each one in water and then in sugar.
Place sugar side up on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet at once.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in tightly covered container.
To serve, use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup of boiling water.

title: marinated beef roast
directions: Brown meat in 1/4 cup butter.
Bake beef at 325° uncovered for 2 hours.
Pour sherry over meat and bake 1 hour more.
Remove meat from oven; cool and slice, saving juice.

title: creamy pecan fudge
directions: Combine
chocolate morsels, marshmallow cream and butter in a large bowl.
Combine sugar and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan; bring
to a boil, reduce heat, and cook over low heat 9 minutes,
stirring
constantly.
Pour
over chocolate morsel mixture; stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Add pecans;
stir
until well blended.
Spread mixture in a lightly buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Chill until firm; cut into
squares.
Cover
and store in refrigerator.
Yields about 10 dozen.
