title: never fail scones
directions: Beat together egg and sugar.
Add 3/4 cup milk and butter. Stir together flour and salt.
Make a well in center and add egg-milk mixture.
Add up to 1/4 cup more milk, if needed, to make a soft dough.
Turn out of bowl onto well-floured board and pat flat to about 3/4-inch thickness.
Using a 1 1/2-inch cutter, cut and place close together on a floured (not greased) baking sheet. Bake at 500° about 10 minutes.
Makes 15 to 18.

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Rinse kidney beans.
Pour into large bowl. Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper thoroughly.
Pour over beans and onion.
Mix well.

title: "crabbies"
directions: When all ingredients are at room temperature; mix.
Cut muffins in half and spread with mixture.
Freeze for 10 minutes. Cut into fours.
(Re-freeze for future use.)
Bake at 325° until bubbly and golden brown.

title: casserole ole
directions: Prepare Velveeta dinner as directed.
Add chilies. Brown and drain meat.
Stir in taco seasoning and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer and simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add Velveeta dinner/chilie mixture to meat mixture. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Before serving, top with sour cream and chopped tomato.

title: jet age gnocches(potato dumplings)
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in instant potatoes.
Gradually stir in enough flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out dough onto a floured surface and knead gently until smooth.
Shape dough into ropes about 1/2 inch in diameter. Cut pieces in oval shapes.
Drop a few at a time into large kettle of boiling salted water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from water with slotted spoon.
Keep gnocchi hot.
Serve with any sauce, butter or cheese.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk; fold into large container of Cool Whip.
Wash, dry, stem and cut up berries; fold into mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate. Serve.

title: white punch
directions: Chill ingredients thoroughly. Mix together in punch bowl.
You can freeze mint leaves in ice rings and float in punch.
Very nice punch for weddings or showers.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix together vinegar, egg and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Makes 2 double and 1 single pie crusts.

title: one dish hamburger meal
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes and rice. Cover; simmer until rice is tender.
Really simple but delicious.

title: fast and easy creamy noodles
directions: Boil about 2 to 3 cups of egg noodles with a little salt until done.
Drain; return to pan on low heat.
Add the soup and 1/2 cup or so of water.
Stir on low heat for about 5 minutes.
This is a great side dish with chicken, beef or pork chops.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; chill until almost set. Blend in whipped topping and raspberries; chill.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Saute lightly the chopped onion, celery, pepper and garlic. Add liquid ingredients, rice, okra, herbs and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add fish and shell fish and simmer an additional 5 to 8 minutes or just until fish is opaque, but tender.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
In creole cooking, standing after cooking is crucial for the fullest flavor.
Serves 4.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and onion through food chopper.
Put in large heavy pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Boil 2 to 3 hours until thick, stirring frequently.
Be careful of settling to bottom and sticking if you don't stir often enough.
Have heat just high enough so it bubbles constantly.

title: chocolate delight (frump)
directions: Melt the butter in a deep baking pan.
Pour on top a batter made of the sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
(No eggs or salt used.)
Have ready the fruit, heated with the extra sugar. Pour the hot fruit on top of the batter.
Bake in the oven at 370° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If raw fruits are used, bake 15 minutes longer.

title: healthy barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Pour off fat that accumulates.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well, and simmer 20 to 30 minutes uncovered.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Yields 6 (1/2 cup) servings, 200 calories.
Low-fat and low cholesterol.

title: toasted pound cake with warm lemon sauce
directions: In small saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch and lemon zest. Gradually whisk in lemon juice and water. Bring to a simmer over low heat, stirring constantly. Set aside.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cut the tomatoes into four pieces and cook in slightly salted water until soft.
Prepare a light roux from butter and flour, thinned with water.
Put tomatoes through a sieve and add to roux. Season to taste.
Bring to a boil.
If sauce is too thick then thin with a few tablespoons of milk.

title: quesadilla
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle chilies and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and guacamole, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic; saute until tender. Add flour, salt and red pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until caramel colored (about 10 minutes). Add broth and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until thick and bubbly. Stir in crawfish and cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with rice.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
After soft ball stage, remove from heat and add the Hershey bars, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream. Add any of the optionals.
Beat with mixer until blended well. Pour into 12 x 9-inch buttered pan. Let cool before cutting.
Makes large batch of fudge.

title: amish barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in crock-pot until hot throughout.

title: love cake for mom
directions: Put chocolate chips in the dough.
Put the dough on those little trays that you put in the oven.
Then you put it in the oven to cook.
Keep the lookout on it so when it's ready you can know.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Saute celery, onion, pepper and garlic in oil until soft.
Add beans, rice, barbecue sauce and pepper sauce; heat through, about 20 minutes.

title: go to church chicken
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together and spread over bottom of greased casserole.
Lay chicken breasts on top of rice; cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and brown before serving.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put hamburger in 2 cups cold water.
Cook on low heat.
Stir until meat is in small pieces; add salt.
Stir in ketchup and cook slowly.
Add chili powder.
Cook dry.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops; drain on paper towels.
In a buttered baking dish arrange potatoes and pork chops.
In a small bowl, combine water and soup mix; pour over meat and potatoes.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 1/4 hours in 350° oven.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In a shallow dish, combine the cornmeal and flour.
Stir to mix.
Sprinkle the tomato slices with salt and black pepper.
Coat with cornmeal mixture. Set aside for a few minutes then coat the slices again with cornmeal mixture. Heat oil (about 1/4 inch deep) in heavy skillet.
If using an electric skillet, set the temperature at 375 degrees. When the oil is heated, place the tomato slices in the oil and fry until crispy and brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: reeses peanut butter squares
directions: Mix well and flatten out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chocolate chips on top.
Put in warm oven until chips melt.
Cut into squares.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into mixing bowl; beat until mashed.
Add rest of ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 15 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and cornmeal.
Pour 1/2 into each unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Layer cucumbers and onions with a handful of salt on each layer in old-time crock.
Mash down.
Cover with ice; let stand 4 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers and onions and return to a boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat.
Cover and continue boiling for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove lid and continue to cook until small amount dropped in cold water forms a small ball.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to pour in a greased square 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: redneck rutabagas
directions: Cut up rutabagas in 3/4-inch pieces.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil, then cut it down to simmer.
Dip grease from top.
Cook until meat can be removed from bone (approximately 1 1/2 hours). Remove pork chops from pot and remove the meat from the bone. Cut up meat into smaller pieces.
Return meat to pot and stir. Cook on low until desired doneness.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna spring salad
directions: Mix olives, carrots, celery, parsley, onion and vinegar in small bowl.
Mix cottage cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tuna.
Mix all together and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Mix well (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients (except rhubarb) with electric mixer until foamy.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes, then in 325° oven for 1/2 hour.
Will form its own crust.

title: fried apple turnovers
directions: Combine the sugar, cinnamon, butter and apples in a saucepan. Simmer this mixture until apples are tender.

title: chicken vegetables and rice
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook carrots, celery and onions about 10 minutes.
Remove vegetables to a bowl. In same pan, heat cut up chicken, parsley, bay leaf, bouillon, salt and 6 cups of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until juices run clear.
Remove chicken to another bowl.
Refrigerate chicken for about 15 minutes; skin and debone.
Cut into bite size.
While chicken is cooling, add vegetables and rice to broth.
Heat to boil.
Reduce to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender.
Add chicken; heat to boiling.
Discard parsley and bay leaf.

title: blueberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello and water until dissolved, then add undrained fruit and nuts.
Fold in unwhipped whipping cream.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Trim
edges
from bread and cut into cubes; saute mushrooms, onions
and
peppers
in
butter.
Combine mayonnaise, mushroom soup,
eggs, milk and salt.
Grease a 2 quart casserole.
Put
in bread cubes.
Mix everything else together and pour over bread. Mix gently.

title: cheese filled meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, eggs, grated onions, parsley, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a bowl.
Shape around cheese cubes, making each meatball about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Heat oil in a large kettle.
Brown meatballs evenly on all sides. Remove.
Keep warm. Saute onions in meat drippings until translucent.
Add tomato juice and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Heat to boiling. Stir in noodles gradually so that liquid continues to boil. Cook 5 minutes.
Add meatballs. Cover and simmer 7 minutes.

title: roast baby pig(a soul food spectacular!)
directions: Note:
Order piglet from butcher several days ahead.
Have eyes, feet and tongue removed at market.

title: golf cart tea
directions: Chill tea before using.
Garnish with cherries and orange slices.
A favorite in Long Island.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Saute until limp, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Blend in flour.
Add parsley, cayenne pepper, Tabasco sauce, salt, tomato paste, tomato sauce, tomatoes and water.
Add bay leaf but remove before serving.
Cook for 30 minutes or until thick.
Stir in shrimp and simmer for 20 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Roast and peel chilies.
Make a 2-inch slit at top and pull out seeds and veins.
Stuff each chili with cheese.
Lightly flour.
Beat yolks and whites separately.
Make whites stiff. Fold together.
Add cream of tartar.
Dip chilies in egg mixture. Fry in 1/2 inch of hot oil.
Turn when brown.
Blot on paper towel.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in baking dish and spoon over chicken breasts.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 1 hour or more.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large pot, fry bacon until brown.
Remove fat from pan. Add corn, milk, celery seed and butter.
Drain potatoes and celery and add to pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until butter melts.
Do not boil.
Better next day.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water, applesauce and raspberries; let harden.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows; let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Use for a topping.

title: peach pie
directions: Crush 3 peaches and add 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water and 3 tablespoons cornstarch.
Cook until the mixture is thick and clear.
Slice the remaining peaches into a baked pie shell.
Pour the cooled mixture over the sliced peaches and chill.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix and store in the fridge.

title: sirloin tips and mushrooms
directions: In a wide skillet, brown the meat in 2 tablespoons oleo and the oil.
Add garlic.
Remove pieces to casserole with a cover as they brown.
Add rest of oleo to skillet. Saute the mushrooms and add to the meat. Cover. Bake, slowly, at 275° for 1 hour, until meat is tender.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix together.
Pour into large pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: lentil soup
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients for 3 to 4 hours.
Steam or saute in butter the garlic, onion, celery and carrots.
Add to lentils and continue to simmer on low heat.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop 1 quart lime sherbet into punch bowl.
Add 12 (7 ounce) bottles lemon-lime carbonated beverage, pouring liquid slowly down side of punch bowl.
Makes 12 to 15 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: grace murray's sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter and Crisco in a large skillet.
Add sweet potatoes and cook over medium heat, turning frequently.
Sprinkle sugar over potatoes and continue cooking until potatoes are soft and the sugar has dissolved.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix together dates, butter, baking soda and water and let cool. Then add other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from tins (tin size 9 x 5 1/2-inch).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion; drain.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Blend well together and roll about 3/4 teaspoon of dough into balls (about walnut size).
Bake on ungreased cookie pan at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Flatten balls of dough lightly with fork dipping fork occasionally in flour to prevent sticking.)
Makes 48 cookies.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat enchilada sauce and V-8 juice to boiling.
Pour 2/3 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fill each tortilla with remaining ingredients.
Then wrap each one.
Place in sauce.
Top with remainder of enchilada sauce, then remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Makes 1 large roll or 2 small rolls.
Keep refrigerated and can be frozen.

title: black raspberry dumplings
directions: In a 6-quart pan, combine raspberries, sugar, water and cornstarch to blend.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Turn heat to low.
Combine baking mix, milk and sugar; mix until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling berries.
Cook over low heat, uncovered, for 10 minutes, then cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until dumplings are cooked through.
Sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar and a dash of nutmeg before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: food processor pie crust
directions: Makes crust for one (9-inch) pie.

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookies in a food processor or in zipper style bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Plant gummy worms or other candy creatures into the cups of "dirt."

title: pecan dainties
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and add remaining ingredients, except pecan halves.
Mix well and chill until firm. Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Arrange on ungreased cookie sheets and top each with a pecan half.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: green chili broccoli
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter. Thaw broccoli and drain well; put into small casserole.
In a separate pan, melt Velveeta; add chilies, onions, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Pour mix over broccoli and mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until it is bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken mozambique peri-peri
directions: Place cut-up chicken in a bowl.
Mix with cumin and lemon juice.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes about 1/2-inch thick.
Dip in flour, salt and pepper to coat both sides.
Fry in hot oil until golden on both sides; drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Good eating!!!

title: cinnamon-applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve candy in hot (boiling) water and then dissolve jello in it. Cool a bit. Add applesauce and pour into mold or dish. Chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Stir together egg and buttermilk; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in onion. Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: marinated lamb kabobs
directions: In bowl, combine all marinade ingredients.
Add lamb cubes and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir from time to time.

title: honey baked beans
directions: Heat oil; add onion and simmer until golden yellow.
Add ground beef.
Stir until browned; add remaining ingredients and pour into bean pot.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mattie's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, adding onions, bell pepper and mushrooms last (all chopped fine). Mix well.
Shape in a loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy spoon rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar, egg, margarine, flour and yeast.
Beat well. Pour into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mutza
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan thoroughly.
Peel and grate potatoes (or use blender).
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Put half of potatoes in bottom of pan.
Mix ground beef, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and onion.
Flatten into thin patties and place over top of grated potatoes in pan.
Try to cover the whole surface of potatoes. Cover with remaining grated potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then grease or oil top surface of potatoes with butter or margarine very well.
Bake another 30 minutes until nicely browned.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan bring to a boil sugar, milk, cocoa.
Stir constantly until it becomes candy stage (when fudge balls up when dropped into cold water).
Add vanilla and margarine, stir rapidly until blended.
Add oats and drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: maryland lady crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently, but thoroughly.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Cook cakes in frying pan in just enough fat to prevent sticking, until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 crab cakes.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine in bowl.
Mix until crumbly.
Set into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: molded cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in marshmallows until dissolved. Add pineapple juice after they dissolve.
Cool until Jell-O begins to set. Add cabbage, pineapple, whipped evaporated milk and mayonnaise. Also add walnuts.
Whip into Jell-O.
Pour into mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve.

title: cantaloupe frost
directions: In blender container, combine milk and melon.
Cover blend until smooth.
Add yogurt, cover and blend until smooth.
Serves four people.

title: chile con queso
directions: Put fruit on kabob sticks.
Alternate different kinds of fruit or make them all one kind.
Serve before the meal.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed.
Let stand 5 minutes, then blend in Cool Whip.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers. Top with remaining crackers and pudding.
Spread pie filling over top.
Chill 3 hours.
Serves 9.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, salt, vanilla and oats.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on aluminum foil on cookie sheets. Cool 1 minute before removing from sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes about a hundred paper thin, crispy cookies.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Spread out in 8 x 12-inch pan and bake 10 minutes. Cool.

title: seven-up cake
directions: No need to frost. Cook in tube pan at 350°.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook broccoli or cauliflower in boiling water until almost tender, about 5 minutes; drain.
(If frozen broccoli or cauliflower is used, do not cook.)
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer.
Mix Ricotta cheese, parsley, eggs and chives.
Put 1 cup of meat mixture in bottom of lasagne pan.
Layer with 1/2 the dry noodles, 1/2 the cheese mixture, 1/2 of the Mozzarella and 1/2 of remaining sauce. Repeat layers again, ending with meat sauce.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before baking in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in a jar or airtight container.
When ready to use, add 1 cup Cocoa Mix to 2 cups water.

title: carrots provencal
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over moderately high heat.
When the oil is hot, add carrots, stir to coat carrots with oil and reduce to moderate heat.
Cover and braise for 20 minutes, stirring regularly.

title: tropical carrot raisins salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins and pineapple in a medium bowl.
Toss well.
Combine yogurt and remaining ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Add to carrot mixture, stirring well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings (85 calories per 1/2-cup serving).

title: dad's apple-cranberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and put aside.
Mix water and juices, put aside.
Mix apples and cranberries.
Put half of apple/cranberry mixture in pie shell and drizzle with half of wet mixture. Drizzle with half of dry ingredients.
Repeat layers.
Cube butter and distribute over top.
Put on top crust and vent by poking holes with a fork (all over crust).
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes, then at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, then add chocolate and vanilla.
Stir good and add flour; stir good, then add pecans.
Bake at 400°.
Test center after 15 minutes cooking with toothpick; if it comes out clean, take out of oven.
Don't overcook.

title: pork oriental
directions: Brown steak and cook about 20 minutes with water, soy sauce, vinegar, honey and brown gravy mix on low heat.
Cook carrots, onions and green pepper 15 to 20 minutes.
Prepare rice according to directions.
Mix all together or serve meat mixture over rice.

title: relish
directions: Mix both together. Serve.

title: peanut cookies
directions: In medium bowl, beat butter and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and salt.
Gradually beat in flour until blended.
Wrap dough and chill 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Scald milk and pour over poppy seed.
Let stand for 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy, add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and poppy seed mixture alternately to cream mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in batter.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread layers and frost cake with filling.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix undiluted fruit juices and water and chill.
Add ginger ale and crushed strawberries just before serving.
Makes 25 half-cup servings.

title: pasta beans
directions: On low heat, fry garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Add tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Bring to boil and simmer 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour, salts and pepper.
Reserve extra flour mixture.
Brown meat in margarine; add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Stir in reserved flour.
Gradually add broth, Worcestershire and catsup.
Bring to boil; add sour cream.
Heat. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: lo-cal lemon salad
directions: Mix in order given and refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown beef.
Let drain.
Grease skillet. Sprinkle bottom with meal and brown in oven.
Mix egg, milk, meal, corn, red pepper and oil together.
Pour half the batter in skillet. Spread meat, onion and cheese over batter.
Then pour other half of batter over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown on top.

title: "wood chuck" chicken casserole
directions: Heat and stir in double boiler the soup, Velveeta cheese and Old English cheese. In separate pan, boil for 8 minutes the celery, pimientos, olive, green pepper and onion juice. Drain and add to double boiler along with chicken and heat to serving temperature. Serve over chow mein noodles. Serves 10.

title: papa's eggplant bake(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Peel and soak eggplant in salted water for 8 hours in the refrigerator.
Drain and cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place eggplant in large saucepan.
Cover with water; bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Drain and place eggplant in shallow, 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Melt butter in medium saucepan over low heat.
Combine onion, garlic, oregano and green pepper in butter until tender.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Cut biscuits in halves.
Shake in sugar mixture and layer in greased Bundt cake pan or angel food cake pan.

title: suzi q's hamburgers
directions: Mix and knead together.
Form patties and fry, adding Worcestershire sauce to top of patties.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into large bowl.
In saucepan, mix oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Mix well and add buttermilk vanilla, salt, cinnamon, soda and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour batter on greased and floured jellyroll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: quick italian soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, corn (with liquid), tomatoes (with liquid) and cheese; break up tomatoes with fork. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles and zucchini.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle each serving with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 9 1/2 cups soup.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve. This can be served frozen too.

title: two lemon pies
directions: Separate eggs; put whites in a small bowl.
Mix lemon juice, condensed milk and egg yolks.
Pour into pie crusts.
Beat egg whites until thick.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff. Spread over pies.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Chill and serve.

title: terrific meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; mold into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and gravy the low-fat way. It freezes beautifully!

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss well and chill thoroughly. Serve on a bed of lettuce.
This can make a delicious sandwich filling.
Makes approximately 3 salad servings or 4 sandwich filling servings.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter over low heat until creamy.
Put corn flakes in bowl and pour on 1/2 of creamy mixture and toss, then add the remainder of creamy mixture and toss to coat flakes.
Spoon on foil.
Let set until cold, then put in tins.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix and chill 24 hours.

title: dorito dip
directions: Layer as listed.
Sprinkle sauce on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut ice cream pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Press 1/2 ice cream into crust.
In a small bowl, mix peanut butter and syrup.
Spread over ice cream. Top with remaining ice cream.
Sprinkle on nuts and freeze.

title: supreme delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Press on the bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Cool completely in refrigerator for several hours (until chilled).

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and let simmer 45 minutes to one hour. Pour over cooked and drained spaghetti.

title: bread pizza
directions: Spread sauce on a piece of loaf bread.
Then put on the cheese.
Add the other topping that you like on your pizza. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until cheese has melted.
This makes a great after school snack.

title: rosemary's dessert or salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: 10 pie pie crust
directions: Place the Crisco, flour and salt into a large bowl.
Use your hands to work the Crisco into the dry ingredients.
Add the water and continue mixing and work into a firm ball.
Divide into 10 balls; wrap and freeze.
Thaw as needed.
Rolls out perfectly every time.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put cranberry juice and apple juice in percolator coffeepot. Put remaining ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk as you would coffee and enjoy.

title: gourmet casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in large skillet; drain.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Continue cooking until vegetables are transparent.
Add uncooked rice, soup, cheese and pimientos.
Mix all well.
Pour in 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or more until rice is tender.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: In mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Melt butter in deep 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Pour mixture in melted butter; do not stir.
Pour in peaches and add cinnamon; do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: curried tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and curry powder in 2-quart casserole. Stir in tuna, noodles, celery, raisins, almonds and 1/2 the onion rings.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Sprinkle on remaining onion rings.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes until heated through.

title: lazy dessert
directions: Mix everthang but applesauce reel gud 'n pack in a square cake pan...add applesauce 'n cook in ice box fur several hours...cut in squares 'n slop on sum whipped cream.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Preheat electric roaster to 400°.
Scale and clean fish leaving head and tail on, if desired.
Combine remaining ingredients for stuffing.
Stuff and truss the fish.
Place in greased casserole.
Place on roaster rack.
Bake in electric roaster at 350° for 1 hour (steam vents open).

title: schmorgan
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Pour into greased 10-inch skillet (with ovensafe handle).
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° for 5 minutes longer.
The finished product will be golden brown with 1/2 to 1-inch sides. Remove from skillet and then brush with melted butter, powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Then serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery in a skillet.
Add tomato soup.
Add Worcestershire.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Butter hamburger buns and broil until slightly toasted.
Spoon on beef mixture.

title: no fuss caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large brown paper bag.
Place brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, vanilla and salt in 2-quart glass bowl or casserole.
Microwave at High setting (100%) 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until mixture comes to a boil. Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour syrup over popped corn in bag.
Close and shake well.
Microwave at High setting 1 1/2 minutes; shake bag well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Shake bag and put caramelized popcorn into large roasting pan.
Cool and stir to separate kernels.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour into buttered dish.
Top with a few crumbs and butter and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly. Stir in coconut.
Press mixture lightly into ungreased 9 x 13 pan, building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg (yolks); drizzle on apples.
(Topping will not completely cover apples.)
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Serve warm.

title: mandarin angel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in 2 layer cake pans or a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cool before frosting.

title: sugar cookies 1
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour.
Put vinegar into a cup and stir in baking soda (it will foam), then add this mix into the batter.
Chill for a day or 2.
Roll out chilled dough. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Shred zucchini coarsely; drain in colander.
Grate onion coarsely.
Combine all ingredients, except oil and seasoned salt. Use only enough flour to hold mixture together.
Heat oil in large Teflon skillet (you may need more oil if not using Teflon).
Drop fritter mixture, a tablespoon at a time, into oil.
Flatten with back of a spoon.
Cook over medium heat until crisp brown; turn and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Can be reheated.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine milk and soup in bowl, mixing well.
Layer potatoes, onion and soup mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Wash the whole carrots.
Trim off the top and small lower end.
Grate each carrot stick until you have one pound of carrot shreds (it measures to about 3 cups). Combine the sugar and vegetable oil in a large bowl.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add this dry combination to the oil mixture, while constantly beating.
Add carrots and nuts and blend well.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: springerlies
directions: Mix well.
If sticky, add small amount flour.
Roll out in confectioners sugar.
Cut and place on cookie sheet.
Let stand overnight, covered.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: garlic grits
directions: Bring water and salt to rolling boil. Add grits. Cook 5 minutes.
Add butter and garlic roll.
Let melt.
Beat egg in measuring cup.
Finish filling with melted butter mixture.
Mix in with grits.
Pour into greased
casserole.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake with rum glaze
directions: Note: Can dust with powdered sugar after baking or cover with Rum Glaze (following).

title: fried chicken
directions: Finely crush crackers.
Remove skin and cut away excess fat from chicken.
Place butter in pie plate; cover with wax paper. Cook at High (100% power) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until butter melts.
On wax paper, mix crumbs, paprika, salt and rosemary.
Dip chicken in butter, then coat with crumbs.
Arrange coated chicken on rack in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook at High for 9 minutes.
Remove wax paper; rotate dish half turn. Cook at High for 5 to 7 minutes longer, until chicken is tender. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: willy's barbecued kraut
directions: In iron skillet, cook and crumble bacon.
In bacon grease, cook onion until tender.
Add 2 cans tomatoes.
Add brown sugar and A.1. sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix in kraut.
Mix and put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over kraut.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orgasmic brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside.
Mix melted butter, cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts (this mixture is thick).
Press half of the dough in pan and bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese-salsa dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave or saucepan.
Add soup, sausage and salsa.
Heat until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips or your favorite chips.

title: favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil and blend well.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Add lemon juice to fish; add rest of ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar and flour.
Soften margarine; knead into the dry ingredients.
Add water if needed to mix.
Mixture should be thick; will not crunch if mixture is soupy.
Put this on top of cooked apples or applesauce.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Cook at 300° for about 45 minutes, or until it is crunchy.
